properties.adr_address: 5226 Shaw Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Longtime Italian spot with pizzas & toasted ravioli delivered in an old-world, elegant atmosphere.

properties.formatted_address: 5226 Shaw Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA
properties.name: Charlie Gitto's On the Hill

reviews.text: One of my favorite St. Louis Restaurants! Food is always fabulous! Whether you come here for dinner during the week or for a special celebration, Charlie Gitto’s on the Hill will not disappoint.  We stopped here tonight on our way to Enterprise Center to see a show.  They knew we were on a time schedule and they were very accommodating.  We had caprese salads, scallops with risotto, seafood risotto and veal parmigiana. Delicious!

Lovely place to dine in. Tim was our server and took good care of us and recommended some great dishes. Loved the shrimp and kalamari appetizers. We had lasagna and baked meatballs for entrees. We were also provided with a complimentary cake slice for my birthday. Recommend getting a reservation on open table, the place gets busy quick.

By far the best old school Italian restaurant vibe on the Hill. Especially if you are seated up in the front room. Last time we were her we got a spot at the bar and that was a cool experience too.

We loved the signature shrimp appetizer, but it's lost a step. They must have changed the sauce recipe a little. Still good, just not as good as we remembered from 6 years prior (we sort of had beef with Gittos after trying to do a wedding dinner here and finally gave in).

Highly recommend for a date night or other special occasion. Reservations help, but we always end up getting seated in under an hour without. Beer selection is solid.

Came here before a show at the fox theatre and it did not disappoint. From the appetizers to the dessert everything was amazing. The food was beautiful and delicious.

The service was awesome our server was attentive and helpful and gave great recommendations.

Pro Tip: There is a parking lot here so you don't have to park in the street!

My wife and I enjoyed a wonderful meal (on a nice big gift card 😀) before catching Hamilton at the Fox in '22. We each ordered an entree and shared an appetizer, and we could barely take a bite of the dessert by the time we got to it. This is definitely a special occasion kind of place for most couples and families with more affordable spots elsewhere on the Hill, but we had a 10/10 experience and I look forward to going back one day!

properties.adr_address: 2225 Macklind Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110-2951, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Easygoing eatery whipping up hearty plates of Italian & Greek fare, including toasted ravioli.

properties.formatted_address: 2225 Macklind Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA
properties.name: Anthonino's Taverna

reviews.text:
We loved dinner here on The Hill! The food was fantastic, overall vibes and service were perfect too! We enjoyed some wine with dinner - started off with the baked goat cheese dip (the pita it came with was so good!) The pesto ravioli was so creamy and delicious, would definitely get this again. The salmon pasta was just alright - the pasta was basically butter noodles but the salmon was cooked perfectly! The pizza had a thicker crust and the mozzarella was yummy on it!
The desserts were the perfect way to end the night (tiramisu and dark chocolate raspberry cheesecake from Hank's) - they definitely stole the show!

Love this place! My wife and I went early in the evening and really enjoyed the family atmosphere. We had the lasagna and the sausage and pasta, it was fantastic. We also had the toasted raviolis.  The pictures are of it half eaten because we couldn’t wait to dig in!

All I can say is that we enjoyed everything we had.  The melted goat cheese & beef toasted ravioli appetizers were a 10 outta 10. I had the pesto chicken which was delicious. The cannolis were just as good as the ones I've had in NYC.
Classic Italian with classy decor. The pizza had a perfect crispy crust and was the perfect amount of cheese. Service was great! Ordered my favorite dessert to go so I could enjoy it later.

Good place with the home feeling. Felt like everyone knew everyone. Our server was super nice and helpful. Tried a dish that I haven't had before and just as our server said, it is delicious and now a favorite of mine! Definitely will eat here again when we are in st Louis.

properties.adr_address: 20 S 4th St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Longstanding, family-owned Italian eatery serving steaks, signature pasta & seafood.

properties.formatted_address: 20 S 4th St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: Carmine's Steak House

reviews.text: This restaurant not only had delicious food, they also provided the best service! Everyone was so welcoming and helpful. Our waiter Logan was the best waiter we have ever had. He took good care of us, was very patient as this was our first time eating here, and was also very personable. My daughter and I split a meal and he was sure to have them plate out meals separately which was such a nice touch. My husband ordered something of the menu and it came out perfect! It was great to see he was training a new staff member because his teachings will be valuable. Logan thank you for starting off our vacation on a great note!

Carmines's was a really nice place and the service was fantastic. I wasn't a big fan of the candied scallops but my wife enjoyed them. My wife loved the carmine steak and I think the ribeye was pretty good, but not great.  The risotto was really, really good and we liked the special garlic potatoes u gratin

A fun, yet sophisticated, atmosphere. I got the 10 oz steak andy partner got the Porterhouse steak. Both food items were excellent. Delicious bread and sides. Our waiter, Logan, made my birthday dinner here special.

Carmine’s appetizer of fried ravioli and dinner of bone-in ribeye and creamy mushroom risotto did not disappoint! The food quality, presentation and taste was outstanding!!! We were recommend to go to Carmine’s by the hotel we stayed in. We did feel grotesquely under dressed and chose not to check our coats because of this. Therefore, we were ushered to the very back room with the rest of the under dressed, coat wearing crowd. I understand they have a dress code which would have been nice to know ahead of time so we didn’t get treated like second class citizens they were embarrassed of. Our waiter, however was very attentive and did an excellent job. The floor manager (I think) came to check on us and the food quality a couple times. I’d definitely go back for the food!!

From the time we walked in to the time we left the service was wonderful! We ordered the lobster bites, shrimp scampi, pepperloin, risotto, Cajun corn, and augratin potatoes, Gouda beer cheese soup.

Skip the potatoes the rest is a must try!
We asked our serve for recommendations and he pulled through. We will be coming back!

properties.adr_address: 736 S Broadway, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Down-home hangout featuring Cajun classics plus nightly live music & a hopping outdoor patio.

properties.formatted_address: 736 S Broadway, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: Broadway Oyster Bar

reviews.text: Fun establishment in downtown Saint Louis. Parking is limited as the lot only has a few spots but paid street parking is available all around. Food was great - try the Alligator Cheesecake, you won’t regret it! I had the Shrimp voodoo tacos with jambalaya as a side and it was good. We also had the fish tacos with rice and beans which was also enjoyed. Live band was playing on a Wednesday evening

Loved it! They were very accommodating with producing dairy free options. They have plenty of meat and fish options on their menu. The flavors, vibe, and employees were nothing short of amazing!  I highly recommend this place for anyone looking for oysters, fish, Cajun,  Louisiana style flavors.
They do have crawfish and gator on their menu. Plenty of seating inside the building or inside their outdoor tent (still warm even with the winter temperatures)
Stop by if you're in town!

I would recommend call for a reservation. Not sure if we just came in during a busy time but the wait was long so we decided to eat at the bar.

Great vibe and atmosphere. Staff was good.

We would recommend the seafood. My spouse definitely enjoyed the oysters and salad. My chicken sandwich paired with the Cajun fries were ok.

Favorite place for shrimp po’ boys and oysters!  Fantastic vibe and excellent service.  Staff is nice and always do a great job.  This is a must visit for anyone coming to St. Louis.  Stop by before a Cards or Blues game, or go at night for live music.  They also have a nice patio for outdoor seating.

Went for lunch on a Monday.  We sat at the bar and were greeted immediately.  I had 10 raw oysters (only $1ea, M-F), and the Shrimp Voodoo Tacos.  My wife had the sampler platter and some sort of creamy cake with a caramel sauce.  The food came out very quickly and it was all delicious; I wish I could eat more. The food here was really, really good.  The decor is fun, Cajun-quirky with a lot of musically-themed artifacts (they have live music 7 days a week).  There's a bit of cool history here, too - some of the original building from 1843 is still in use.  Maybe my new favorite restaurant in St. Louis.  Will definitely return!

properties.adr_address: 1111 Mississippi Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Celebrated bistro for Californian cuisine with a wine emphasis in a stylish renovated-factory space.

properties.formatted_address: 1111 Mississippi Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA
properties.name: Eleven Eleven Mississippi

reviews.text: This is one of my favorite restaurants in St. Louis. This area of St. Louis is very historic, and it’s just a cool place in general. The bartender there Amanda is absolutely fabulous. And their servers are on point with everything. I have never ever had bad service, or bad food at this restaurant. It’s the place to go if you want to take guests when they visit from out of town. Or if you just want to hang out at the bar and have a nice drink. They also have an outstanding patio.  Also, they always have pretty good specials.

We had a birthday dinner here and we really enjoyed it! The steak was cooked perfectly and our mock tails were delicious. Our waiter was a great guy and gave us great recommendations which we ended up choosing like the steak and mussels.

We were looking for a restaurant with a patio and decided on Eleven Eleven Mississippi in the historic LaFayette Square area.  Food was really good.  Highly recommend the Wild Boar Ravioli appetizer…it was amazing.  The patio did not disappoint.  Service was decent.  Looking forward to going back!

Very neat restaurant. Really nice waitress. The food was good with the exception of the salmon, it was slightly undercooked for my liking - so make sure to let them know if you want the center cooked more than raw.

When your in St. Missouri this is definitely a restaurant that you need to visit. The food was amazing, as well as the service. If you like fish you need to try their rainbow trout, the Pettit stake was stake was cook to perfection, and their sides don't fall behind. This was an amazing food experience in Missouri

properties.adr_address: 4260 Forest Park Avenue Entrance On Boyle, At Corner Of, Duncan Ave, St. Louis, MO 63108-2811, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Sleek eatery for local, seasonal cuisine highlighting vegetables & sustainably raised meats.

properties.formatted_address: 4260 Forest Park Avenue Entrance On Boyle, At Corner Of, Duncan Ave, St. Louis, MO 63108, USA
properties.name: Vicia

reviews.text:
I had one of the most memorable dining experiences of my life at Vicia. My husband treated me to dinner at Vicia for my birthday, and we both indulged ourselves with the Farmer's Feast menu.

I really enjoyed watching the staff work in the kitchen - it is obvious that perfection in taste, quality, and presentation are paramount to the restaurant. We thoroughly enjoyed every dish presented to us. What a special experience!

We recommend adding on an upgraded wine package to your meal, it is worth it.

I dined by myself the week of my birthday. I had a fantastic time. I really loved the decor. It's upscale inviting...warm and classic. Kyle, the host with the most, was awesome, pleasant, conversational and even sent me a copy of my menu after my experience. It really meant a lot to me that he thoroughly communicated with me throughout my reservation process, at the initial greeting, leading up to the meal, during the meal and at close. I had fantastic service during my entire experience.

I was seated at the bar.  Danielle was working at the bar and made my experience very worth while.  The wine som that goes between their restaurants was also there that night and it added a lot to the meal. She talked about pairings and the wine itself and I really enjoyed it.

There are a lot of things pictured. I tried to capture how it was placed in front of me...and then I moved things together them in the same frame. I enjoyed everything in the app round.  The pork was the only thing I wasn't thrilled about on the second round... I wish I had more room in my body to finish the corn. It was delicious. Everything was delicious. The elegance and decor were phenomenal.  I highly recommend this experience

Check it out for a true feast.

While the execution of some of the dishes wasn't quite perfected, across the board we had a solid, produce-forward meal. Some dishes needed more acid, some pepper and a few salt, however the creativity and the freshness overshadowed the small missteps. In particular the pesto and the dessert were the stars.

I was afraid the tasting menu wouldn't be filling enough but I was wrong! I had leftovers.

The dessert wine add on was the best value and there is free parking across the street for dinner.

Food is not worse the money. $400 for 2
The staff is exceptional, kind, attentive, chatty as needed and very friendly. Wine paring is totally worth it. Very interesting varieties to f wine. Food…it is possible that we got not into the best week, but why should any week be better or worse than the other. Chef has a strong romance with balsamic reduction & vinegar of one kind or another. It was everywhere..completely overpowering the whole pattern: in three out of five snacks (appetisers - beets, squash, mushroom tacos), in main course- carrots, chicken, salad, and….tam tam tam, wait for it, even the desert…We picked pescatarian menu first, but was convinced to open my options for no restrictions menu. Disappointed as having chicken next day after thanksgiving is not what I thought Chef’s choice was going to be. My favourite plates were the bread from Winslow, radish with pesto, pear in prosciutto, rice that came with main course.

My husband and I opted for the extended tasting menu with a wine pairing...I highly recommend this! The experience was like a stream of tapas all evening long so I didn't leave stuffed. Each appetizer was unique in flavor, but the combination of plates offered never competed with the flavors of the others. The food preparation was a feast for the palate as well as the eyes! I recommend sampling something from the cocktail menu as well! The staff is very personable and knowledgeable...they truly know how to make this a beautiful and comfortable experience! I highly recommend Vicia and can't wait to visit again!

properties.vicinity: 4260 Forest Park Avenue Entrance On Boyle, At Corner Of, Duncan Avenue, St. Louis

properties.adr_address: 3037 Locust St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Former Stutz auto showroom with classic American eats, specialty ice cream drinks & art deco murals.

properties.formatted_address: 3037 Locust St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: The Fountain on Locust

reviews.text: Pretty neat place. Has both alcoholic beverages and dessert, which is the best of both worlds. I got the root beer float with vanilla ice cream. They make their own sodas so it was pretty unique. I enjoyed the atmosphere and would highly recommend to visit this area. Family friendly.

A friend recommended this spot because of its fun atmosphere. Parking was easy and we were seated right away. I had the pickle soup and the Signature Mixed Salad Sandwich. The soup was OK, the pickle flavor is more than I thought but I wanted to try it either way. The sandwich was cheesy and delicious. We didn't have much time so we didn't enjoy dessert. We'd come back to check out the dessert menu! Tim was our server and he did a great job!

Not an expansive menu and no kids menu but the food we got was tasty.  The service was good.  The ice cream shakes were excellent as to be expected.  Definitely no complaints here.  It’s not unreasonably priced for the quality.   We would likely return if we were local.  As traveling through we are glad we stopped.

This is my new favorite place in St Louis! Alex is an excellent server and everything we tried on the menu was fantastic. The dill pickle soup was surprisingly delicious and really did pair well with the Cuban sandwich. For drinks I had the bees knees, love potion No. 9 and the espresso martini. Everything exceeded expectations and I very much look forward to going back

I went back and it was just as amazing as the first time. This time Andrew was taking care of us and was so friendly and energetic. We started with a piping hot spinach and artichoke dip that was super creamy and cheesey. I had the birdseed salad with chicken and was pecking on that while I enjoyed four fabulous drinks. Still my favorite place in St Louis and I loved the Soap Hospital in the booth.

Fabulous spot for for drinks, dessert, and socializing. The food is splendid. I had the famous Adult Grilled Cheese and I’d have it again. The Fountain has a huge selection of unique and well crafted drinks; they also have all your traditional cocktails prepared by skilled mixologist.

properties.adr_address: 2800 Shenandoah Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Cozy, brick-lined restaurant offering seasonal small plates & hearty mains, plus cocktails & wine.

properties.formatted_address: 2800 Shenandoah Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA
properties.name: Little Fox

reviews.text: Great experience and loved that they have many options to do a family style kind of dining. We had an appetizer and then several small plates plus a few round of drinks. Our server had excellent recommendations on pairings and they had a really interesting natural wine selection. Excited to go back and try a few of the main dishes as well

A really creative and delicious menu. Every item we ordered was 10/10 including the cocktails. Fresh, high quality ingredients cooked perfectly. Knowledgeable staff and well designed restaurant. A true gem of the St. Louis food scene.

The second you walk in the first thing you notice & feel are the good vibes of Little Fox. The colors are fresh & modern, but feels old school in a way. The service was outstanding. I could not have asked for a better experience with the couple of staff members I interacted with, they were knowledgable, respectful, funny, & just great at what they do. Now the food was next level. My fiancée & I ordered 2 starters, a small plate (that was bigger than small), & the pork chop. We loved every single dish. Everything was perfectly seasoned & cooked. We were about 90% done & were absolutely stuffed, but we unbuttoned our pants and fought the good fight. 10/10 & will be one of my first stops when I come back to St Louis.

I am excited to post this review AND share with my local foodie friends this new find.  NEVER would have stumbled on the Little Fox, but someone gave us a gift certificate and I am so happy they did.   We walked in and the place was hip and cozy with a ton of positive energy.  There are two large rooms, the front one has an incredible bar.  Do not miss having a cocktail especially one of their original creations.  We had the Love Shack and The Transaction Report both a play on popular cocktails.  For food we started with the Gem Salad which was beautifully presented, perfectly dressed and best of all Chilled.  It was perfectly cold like a salad should be.  We then had the Cannellini Crostini.  I am not one for "bruschetta" but this was one with outstanding taste and texture.  We then had the Bolognese Bianco which was served with a bucatini a great choice of pasta with the texture to hold up to the rich, meaty sauce.  We finished with the Blueberry Cake which I highly recommend as well.  Service was outstanding which is such an important part of dining out.  We were splitting everything as we like to try as many things as we can and they cut the Crostini in half and even split a glass of wine which was incredibly thoughtful but not necessary.  My only issue was the first course came out blazingly fast and we had barely taken the first sip from our cocktails and would have liked 5-10 minutes of enjoying my cocktail before eating.  I CANNOT wait to go back.  Thank you for a wonderful evening.
Incredible restaurant, service was excellent, drinks were unique but great, and food was so tasty. I loved everything I tried. One of my new favorite restaurants in St. Louis.

properties.adr_address: Lower Level of Drury Inn, 201 S 20th St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Longstanding, family-owned Italian eatery serving steaks, signature pasta & seafood.

properties.formatted_address: Lower Level of Drury Inn, 201 S 20th St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Lombardo's Trattoria

reviews.text:
Amazing food and service. My first time at the spot. It was my wife's birthday and in my reservation (having not been familiar with the establishment) I requested a window seat and pre-arranged birthday dessert. Well being on the lower level, there were zero window seats, but the manager, Daniel, took great care of us. He sat us at a mirror section, which was the best alternative. Our service was amazing and food was delicious. Absolutely the best steak and potatoes I've had to date. The birthday dessert was complimentary and my wife loved it as well. I will be back and have already recommended Lombardo's to multiple family members while having after dinner cocktails. Thanks for a great birthday dinner for my wife. Daniel even took pictures of us together for her birthday photo memories!

Excellent job!

Everything was pretty good, just nothing that had any wow factor. Started with the portabella mushrooms which were marinated in balsamic (delicious) and on top of some very salty steamed spinach. Main course pasta was home style Italian, nothing dressed up, just classic stick to your ribs food. Last up was the mile high chocolate cake, decently most and proper rich. Service seemed distracted but still polite, dining area was clean, menus had some bits of food on them. For the price, definitely not impressed, but not disappointed either.

We try to make sure every time we are back in Saint Louis we always go here because literally they have the best toasted ravioli in the city! Chris, the bartender is hilarious and ALWAYS top notch! (PAY HER MORE, SHES WORTH IT)  From start to finish it's always an amazing time and always worth the stop, YOU GOTTA TRY IT...YUMMMMM. I wish I could give this place 6 Stars!

Truly delicious food. Will definitely be coming back here!! I can’t remember the server’s name, but they were fun and polite and I was really happy with their service.
I got a spiked bellini cocktail which was incredible. Then we got the toasted ravioli, which of course was delicious too. Lombardo’s restaurants have the best ravioli in STL, hands down. I used to work at Angelo’s Taverna and they were amazing there, too (PS, definitely recommend if you want a nice italian meal without getting ultra dressed up; Lombardo’s Trattoria is an upscale Italian restaurant)!
I had the Rigatoni Seafood as my entree and the scallops melted in my mouth, the shrimp were delicious, and the creamy lobster sauce was out of this world!! I am practically counting down the days I go back there.
For dessert we shared a chocolate cake, which was huge, rich, and also delicious.
10 stars, incredible.

Our waitress was phenomenal, so sweet. but the food was terrible. I paid $48 for a filet mignon that was no near worth the cost. It was dry no flavor and the outside was burnt. The potatoes were soggy and cold like they had been sitting out for awhile and also no flavor. The bread was literally hard as a rock on the whole bottom side so you could only rip some off the top. I use to eat here all the time and I loved it but I won't be going back

properties.vicinity: Lower Level of Drury Inn, 201 South 20th Street, St. Louis

properties.adr_address: 5100 Daggett Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Local farm-fresh ingredients & daily-changing American menus in a polished bistro setting.

properties.formatted_address: 5100 Daggett Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA
properties.name: J. Devoti Trattoria (Formerly Five Bistro)

reviews.text:
The food and cocktails were amazing!!

The ingredients were fresh and bursting with flavor!!

I had the specialty pizza of the day with morel mushrooms.

I also had an Aviator cocktail which is pictured

The service was excellent

Food is perfect. The menu is set, I wasn't able to find it online before we went so it was a surprise. They accommodated a vege option for us that was good.
The price point is high. $60/plate. The ambiance is under par. A combination of music, people at the bar, loud talking in the kitchen wasn't ideal.
Overall, delicious and high-end experience.

We have a few "go-to" places that we can reliably depend upon. We've been 100% ok with the sort of quirky way this restaurant has been run, and have generally loved the food. Our last meal, however, was a huge disappointment. Our daughter was in town from college and we took her out to celebrate. The apps (and wine) were excellent, but the main course (ribs) were IMO inedible. They were both tough and so salted it was akin to some kind of thick jerky. None of us ate more than one bite. We had tickets at the Fox that night, so we really didn't have time to try for a replacement dish. I figured I'd call the restaurant, let them know the experience, and they'd make it right. So I called the following week. Never got a call back. Since they have a unique schedule, I thought I'd go the extra mile and just share my experience via email (to their general info inbox). Again, no reply. They pop up in my Insta fee a LOT, so I KNOW they are active on Insta. I sent them a quick "I bet you didn't see the email" message on Insta...again...nothing. We won't be back. A $200 life lesson for me.
Thoroughly enjoyed our dining experience at J. Devoti! Everything was locally sourced and delicious. Will definitely be back. Buon appetito!

We got the prix fixe 6 course dinner with wine pairings! If we could rate this 4.5 stars I would. The service was very good and we consistently got each pairing with the food (albeit a couple minutes after the food came each time). I would have loved to hear from our server why they paired each wine with the dish.

The food itself was also very good, just the right size portions to make you full at the end without being stuffed. We loved the pappardelle, salmon tartare and chocolate dessert most! One minor suggestion is to use more acidity in the dishes throughout to make them pop. Thanks for hosting us for our special anniversary.

properties.adr_address: 2199 California Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Cozy, vegan-friendly eatery serving Asian-fusion fare, including make-your-own rice-paper wraps.

properties.formatted_address: 2199 California Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA
properties.name: Lona's Lil Eats

reviews.text: Great place in fox park! Really enjoyed walking over the other night from our Airbnb. Prices are reasonable, service was excellent, and the overall friendly vibe made this a great experience. Adult beverages are for sale as well. The menu is varied with several vegan and vegetarian options of their Asian fusion cuisine. As always, you simply can’t go wrong with smoked brisket. A real must try if you’re in the area!

I was excited to visit Lona's for the first time and try some of their rice-paper-wrapped creations. Unfortunately, the night I visited, they had run out of rice paper! Yes, really.

I ordered the spicy tofu wrap (on a tortilla, unfortunately) with spicy eggplant and an order of mushroom dumplings. The tofu wrap was good, tortilla and all. Delicious blend of flavors with the spice, the cilantro, the sweet cabbage... I could eat that every day. I bet it's even better on rice paper. 😝

The dumplings were also addictive. Savory, with a spicy sauce. Either item probably would have been enough on their own.

I appreciated the dedication to minimizing waste by setting chopsticks aside to be washed and reused. I'm not clear on the wisdom of serving everything on butcher paper, but okay. 🤷 I'll be back another day to try the rice paper.

reviews.author_name: Jody Parrish, Realtor with The Parrish Team
reviews.text: This was an amazing experience! The food was great! We tried several different things and they were all wonderful. My favorite was the turkey with the Lona Q sauce. The staff was unbelievably helpful. Since it was our first time there they even talked us through all of the options.

Love, love, love it! Was my 1st time there, the service was great, everyone was friendly & personable especially the cashier & it had a home feel to it & the food was delicious! And if you can have it, don't forget to get some "Punch"! I will definitely be back!

I liked this place a lot. The giant rice paper wraps were delicious and stuffed full. The stir fried veggie was bok choy, which I liked, and the spicy eggplant was okay. My husband really enjoyed his Thai chicken wrap.

The only real drawback for me is that they don't seem to know what to do with a kid's palate. We talked about using plain tofu, which I got and enjoyed, but my kid's plate had spicy tofu. It's pretty dang spicy, and she just couldn't eat it. He very nicely agreed to bring out non-spicy tofu, but unfortunately it was soaked in some very strong soy sauce. Also, note that even though they have a kid's section on the menu, they apparently don't really have a kid's menu. He mentioned that, but I guess I didn't understand that the "tofu" in that section was the same as the "spicy tofu" on another part of the menu. All this to say: be very explicit if you have strong preferences or dietary needs, particularly if you have a finicky eater in the group.

properties.adr_address: 550 N 7th St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Thai classics like curry, chicken satay & pad kee mao offered in a bright space with playful decor.

properties.formatted_address: 550 N 7th St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Aubergine

reviews.text:
Great food and friendly service. They say about themselves "Thai with a twist", which is true.
We stopped by on a Thursday evening, the place was not too crowded and we could choose our table ourselves, which was nice. We had a couple of questions concerning the menu and the waitress explained it all very friendly to us.
So we had the vegetarian garden spring rolls as a starter and afterwards the red curry with chicken and also a yellow curry, which was on the special menu. The food is freshly prepared, good sized portions and most important delicious.
As drinks we had the Thai Ice Tea, also great, especially with the Thai food.
Last not least I'd like to mention, that the atmosphere in the restaurant is very nice, very bright, open and airy.
Definitely 5*

I enjoyed a relaxing vibe and clean restaurant that serves a nice twist on some traditional dishes.  The food would have recieved five stars had the chicken in the curry dish not been too dry and lacking flavor.  The apps were good, and fried items cooked at the right temp, so not too oily.  The menu is simple, but I am guessing that due to lack of labor to complete preparations the night before, they were out of several menu items  when I arrived at opening for lunch. So that was a bit disappointing.
The food was delicious! They were really busy, so it was a little slow but totally worth it! We are visiting from Wisconsin and I wish we had this restaurant there. We would be there all the time!

Good portions & prices, friendly staff, delicious food, convenient location, airy clean environment. Very impressed!! Got dumplings, coconut shrimp, and chargrilled eggplant (ate before I got a pic). Saved as a fav!

I loved this place! I had a curry noodle dish Kao Soi and my wife got the basil chicken. They were both amazing. The crab rangoon were savory, which is exactly what I hope for in a rangoon. The Tom yum was delicious, they say clear broth but if you've ever had an actual clear (no haze no red) Tom yum that isn't what this is. All the same I would order it all again if I didn't have so many things on the menu I want to try. I definitely recommend this place if you like Thai food.

properties.adr_address: 1000 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Modern, sculpture-filled Thai restaurant serving carefully plated noodles, curries & more.

properties.formatted_address: 1000 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Sen Thai Asian Bistro

reviews.text:
One of my favorite spots downtown, a very well balanced menu selection from appetizers (calamari 2nd pic), entrees (Pad Ginger w/ Beef), sushi and they even offer gluten free menu! They also have a well rounded of cocktails and beer, I always enjoy the plum wine. And they do offer happy hour specials, a kids menu and dessert menu.

During happy hour I’d expect to spend $10-$25, my meal here I was exceptionally hungry so appetizer, entree, sushi, drink = $51. And service was exceptional very intuitive in my experience and was very knowledgeable with the questions involving sake and unfamiliar menu items for my experience.

I was kinda in a hurry, but I was generally impressed with this little place. Fast service, and good food. The rice was perhaps a touch dry, but I really enjoyed my Japanese dish (can't spell it), and my friend enjoyed his  as well. Be warned, they do get very spicy.

Great Asian food in a funky downtown setting. The food was freshly made and delicious. I had the Tonkatsu ramen and the portion was huge. The pork roll was slightly over-cooked but three slices were provided and the marinated egg was delicious. I also had hot sake and a pork belly bao.

There were plenty of food and drink options: noodles, fried rice, sushi, etc. The service was solid. Overall, a great lunch experience and a great find for our short St. Louis trip.

I found out about this restaurant through a friend via Facebook. He had a friend gathering there and I saw the layout of the place and pictures of the food. I was instantly intrigued and happy to see that it was an Asian Bistro. I hadn't been to one in a while since my favorite one, Tani Sushi Bistro had closed in Clayton a few years ago.

I decided that I needed to check out this place and brought my mother along with me. We arrived around 2:30pm and were immediately seated. It was busy so we got there at a great time. We looked over the menu and decided on the following items:

Drinks:
Plum Blossom (Me)
Hot tea (Mom)

Appetizers:
Thai Spring Rolls
Crab Rangoon

Main course:
Pineapple Fried Rice with Shrimp
Three Kings with Shrimp
Tempura Fried JB Roll
Oriental Fried Rice with Chicken

Our drinks first came out along with glasses of water. I swirled my drink around before taking the first sip and it was delicious! The Plum Blossom drink consists of Plum Wine mixed with Club Soda and Chambord liqueur. It had the perfect mix of sweet and carbonation. I had to stop myself from drinking it all up so quickly.

My mom informed me that she was pleased with her hot tea.

Then our appetizers came out. I tried a Thai Spring Roll and it was so light and fluffy! When I bit into the roll it felt like crispy paper. Yet the flavor was definitely there. It didn't feel oily like I'm used to getting an egg roll from a Chop Suey restaurant. The Sweet and Sour dipping sauce also complimented the rolls perfectly.

The other appetizer was Crab Rangoon. The texture was a bit more crispy on these but I'm used to that when it comes to this dish. What really sold me though was the cream cheese mixture of crab, green onion, and bell pepper. The seasoning for this had just the right amount of sweetness without being overpowering.

Finally our main courses came out and I immediately tried a piece of my JB Roll. In other sushi bistro restaurants in Saint Louis normally this dish is called a Philly Roll. It consists of Salmon, cream cheese and avocado. Normally when I order this roll I have them hold the avocado and I request for it to be tempura-fried. I also ask for extra eel sauce to dip my roll.

On my first bite I knew I had found my new favorite place to enjoy sushi. The size of the ingredients in the roll were just right. It didn't feel mushy and it didn't look rushed. It was absolutely perfect. I enjoyed a few more pieces before moving on to my Pineapple Fried Rice.

Now onto my Pineapple Fried Rice with Shrimp......when I took my first bite I feel as though I should have been enjoying this on a beach. This did not have the greasy taste that one might find from a Chop Suey joint. This rice was so fresh. It reminds me of the Japanese styled steakhouses that prepare the food in front of you. It just tasted that fresh. The Pineapples in the dish were complimented with raisins, cashews, egg, green onion, white onion, and carrots and garlic. When I tell you this is by far the BEST fried rice I have ever encountered...I am not saying that lightly.

My mother was very please with her Three Kings dish. She said the seasoning was perfect and she did like snapping the fried noodles into her dish.

I also decided to get a dish to go for my father which was Oriental Fried Rice with Chicken. He let me know that he thought the dish was amazing.

The only negative I have about the experience was about parking. Yet that is not a reflection on the restaurant at all. For myself I was able to find a parking spot right across from the restaurant which I count as a blessing. Because normally parking downtown sucks.

Overall the food here was excellent and I definitely will be revisiting again.

I was in St. Louis for the weekend and was looking up Thai food places. I definitely recommend checking this place out. Their spicy calamari is unique and has immense flavor. I also ordered the Pork Belly Ramen, it's one of the best ramen I've had so far.

Their service is very welcoming. Everything is delightful. My fiancé and I enjoyed our dinner there.

properties.adr_address: Restaurant, 1501 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Casual Italian eatery serving wood-fired pizzas, pasta & meat plates, plus cocktails & draft beer.

properties.formatted_address: Restaurant, 1501 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Ultima Cucina

reviews.text: Excellent food. The chicken parm was superb. The salad was exceptionally tasty....spinach, goat cheese, lightly candied walnuts, and apple slices with a vinaigrette. It was a genuine winner! There was a bit of a wait to get in but worth it and we were treated well.

Great looking place, great ambiance, perfect service, but the food is lacking. My son got the filet mignon and they cut it up. Great for presentation, but not to keep heat in or the juices from flowing before you are ready to eat it. My daughter got spaghetti and the sauces was a fail. How you can mess up spaghetti is beyond me. I guess it's too hard to try to keep it authentic instead of premade.

Forgot our drink order, forgot our appetizer,, sandwiches were subpar and fries undercooked. The kitchen staff could be heard getting into arguments.
The AC was nice on this hot day though.

The food was amazing! Drinks were great and not weak. It is a little pricey, but not overly so considering its a hotel restaurant. Staff were very friendly, but did seem more concerned about wrapping silverware rolls than efficient service. We had to ask where our drinks were after observing an idle bartender and 15 minutes had passed with only getting water. Then not all drinks were brought. Food came a few minutes later complete and accurate. We were surprised at the automatic 20 percent gratuity added to our party of 6's bill which was not in the menu or posted.

Even if you’re a local, you need to eat here!

I got the classic burger, tasted delicious! The fries were basic but perfectly crispy and just yum!

My husband got the margarita pizza and could not stop raving about it!
He said it’s the best margarita pizza he has ever had!
We will definitely be coming back! Maybe for breakfast or dinner!

properties.adr_address: 4261 Manchester Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA
properties.formatted_address: 4261 Manchester Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA
properties.name: Sauce on the Side

reviews.text: Absolutely delicious! Always hear about this place on the radio, but we lived to far away to casually go. When I came to the city I took my family to dine in and everything was very clean, friendly staff and food was perfect!

I appreciated there was a vegan option! I got the Skinny V. My only complaints are that I wish the toppings were a little more spread out. I also wasn’t a fan of the whole garlic cloves, they were a bit toooo much. Overall though, really good. My family really enjoyed it and definitely would come back.

Maybe they were having an off day or something. I was not pleased with my meal at all, it was quite dry and not very flavorful in my opinion.  I probably would not come back.  Great service and good presentation though.

This. Place. Is. Fantastic!  Came to visit StL from Nashville TN, and it was just as good as I remembered.  The Duke & Fatty B are both excellent choices.  The craft sodas really add to the uniqueness.  If you haven't been, you need to go!

Great location, and very pretty and enjoyable environment. Lots of options for a variety of pallets. Tried the Carmen calzone, and it was delicious. Even got offered a refill at the table, excellent service.

properties.adr_address: 2211 Market St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Branch of a local chain of casual American spots serving fried shark & chicken, pizza & burgers.

properties.formatted_address: 2211 Market St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Syberg's On Market

reviews.text: Everything about this place was so yummy!!! We was on spring break vacation and decided to go to a St Louis chain restaurant and I’m so glad we chose this place. The wings were very good and the shark bites (tenders) were made from scratch and tasted like heaven!!! The adult drinks wasn’t very strong but they were very flavorful! We will definitely be going back!
Very nice atmosphere. Loved that they had patio seating,, was such a nice day. Hostess and Waitress very FRIENDLY & COURTEOUS.  Would come back again!!

They were rude from the moment I walked through the door. From the host Mi (she didn’t wana give me her name) to the server mya ! (Both as pictured) the food was so bland. It was old I had to send it back ! The manager Keith tried to make it better by making sure I was okay but the whole experience was ruined! We did had a good server (new girl) name Ali (not sure how to spell it ). I would not ever return to this location!

15% service charge anytime after 6 pm! Is this normal in the St. Louis area? Food was alright, pretty plain. Also, my bill was 33, and some change. So, my change after paying with $40 on a $33 and change bill was $5.

We were recommended this place by our hotel clerk as we was staying in St. Louis. Without hesistation, he gave us Syberg's as an answer for a nearby sports bar in the city. As soon as you walk in, you're greeted with the atmosphere of where locals come to watch the game if they couldn't make it into the stadiums down the street. St. Louis sports memoribilia, neon bar signs and wide screen TVs adorn the walls, making sports and beer the primary focuses of the bar.

That's not to say it isn't worth going for the food: We tried their in-house Whiskey sauced wings, that had a good crispy outer skin and a tangy, finger licking aftertaste. I enjoyed the Open-faced French Dip (without provolone, not too much of a cheese guy) on a toasted garlic roll. The au jus dip was savory, and I wish I soaked my sandwich in it more than I had.

Overall, I would recommend this place to local and traveller alike, and try to visit on a game day! We had stopped in during their trivia night, which still seemed like a fun time. We ended up kind of playing along as we ate.

Actual Rating: 5/5

Atmosphere: 5/5
Food: 5/5
Service: 4.5/5

properties.adr_address: 4457 Gravois Ave, St. Louis, MO 63116-2443, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Cheery, colorful bistro offering upmarket Bosnian fare in a relaxed, bright setting.

properties.formatted_address: 4457 Gravois Ave, St. Louis, MO 63116, USA
properties.name: Taft Street Restaurant & Bar

reviews.text: Very yummy! Was heading to The Heavy Anchor for a show and needed some dinner near by. Found this little place and the goat cheese fritters and seafood ravs were to DIE for! Staff was very friendly and we will be back for more!

This is a gem. The food is interesting & delicious. The space is comfortable. And the server was patient with our many selections. I suggest a long Saturday lunch by a window in the sun with a bottle of wine. Highly recommend it.

We tried the fried chicken wings, chicken tenders, and the fried mushrooms. The mushrooms were the best among the three, while the chicken tenders were also good. The food was not as good as our expectation.

Sweet little restaurant! We were in the mood for something new, & Google found this great Bosnian-owned place nearby.  We're grateful for all the good reviews: they did not let us down.
The portions were GEN-ER-OUS! The service was quick & we got the chance to chat with the owner; an amazing, friendly, & wise gent. The flavors were simple, and the food was cooked perfectly.
Highly recommend it if you want a comfortable, home-cooked-style meal without any family drama. 😁

I called the restaurant Monday at 1pm to see if they can accommodate the party of 16 for dinner that night. The owner was extremely nice and said yes. We came around 7pm. We had the most amazing service and food that we ever had. We would be coming there again. Big thank you to the owner that made this all happen.

properties.adr_address: 2700 Olive St, St. Louis, MO 63103-1426, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Classic Italian & American fare served in a historic space with a relaxed vibe & weekend live music.

properties.formatted_address: 2700 Olive St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Beffa's Bar & Restaurant

reviews.text: We enjoyed out brunch at Beffa’s on a Sunday the place has a decent crowd. There was not a wait for a party of two but we did see larger parties waiting. Even with a staff shortage everything came out quickly. The mimosas were so good and had great flavor options. The chicken sandwich was amazing full of flavor with a great sauce. The chicken and waffle was also good! Great location and parking

This bar was super cute and away from the high traffic areas. Had plenty of parking and was easy to get to. Signage to get into the building was lacking but I found my way in through the side door. I got the French dip and it was so good! My friend got the burger which was a bit messy and got the bun a bit soggy but was overall good! Minus 1/2 star due to the soggy burger and 1/2 star due to the door being a bit hard to find. Other than that service was SPECTACULAR and the french dip was so good!! I would come back here again! And can’t wait to come back for brunch sometime!

On my lady's actual birthday, we went with a friend to this restaurant to continue celebrating. We had checked out Beffa's online to look at the menu. We found that chicken and waffles was on the brunch menu. This is a favorite of MJ's, so we had to try it.

The food did not disappoint. MJ enjoyed her selection. Our friend loved her French Toast dish. I found the smash burger to be delicious. We enjoyed our time there and found the service to be excellent. Football was on the two televisions in this sports oriented location. Even if you don't like sports, this place is worth trying out.

We love this place!  Great specials (especially the burger and beer Fridays), good happy hour and yummy food.  Service has always been good as well.  We finally tried brunch and it did not disappoint.  This is definitely a hidden gem, go check it out!!

Plenty of parking on the back lot. The bar is decorated nicely. The light is low with a welcoming vibe. The staff were so nice! I ordered the Fish Sammich, it was huge & delicious!! Well seasoned. The pub chips were just okay.

They don’t have a soda gun so the sodas come out in cans and lemonade was in a 20oz bottle. They will give you a glass of ice to go with it. I’m not sure about “refills” but someone else in my party had a can of Coke and when she finished it, the waitress brought her another one immediately. I had the 20oz bottle of lemonade and did not receive a second one, so I imagine it wouldn’t be sustainable to just keep handing those out. It did make me pace myself for sure. I’m not mad at the process.

I would eat here again for sure!

properties.adr_address: 2000 Sidney St, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Inventive New American cuisine served in a sophisticated but comfy setting with exposed-brick walls.

properties.formatted_address: 2000 Sidney St, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA
properties.name: Sidney Street Cafe

reviews.text: I haven't ever done this, but I liked it so much, I went back the next night to eat there again! If you can, get their tartare, and order the polenta with whatever else is going to make you happy. Either (or both) salad and soup (creamy and flavorful squash soup! Amen!) will make you glad you chose them. The brisket is smoky and falls apart in the very best way. The scallops are tender and tasty. The dessert items and accompanying libations are a wonderful and worth it splurge. On your own, or a small party without a reservation? Try sitting at the bar, where the bartenders are ready with interesting conversation and insightful menu suggestions. 11/10 on a scale of 10.

⭐️Delectable, Decadent, Delicious! 😋 (D³)⭐️

This was probably one of the BEST meals I've ever had. Kudos to the chef, kitchen staff, owner, bartender... basically the entire staff/establishment. For those that have not tried this amazing spot in downtown STL, I very highly recommend! 👌 🙌

One of the finest culinary experiences in STL! Nestled near Benton park/ Soulard area - a nondescript building from outside but as soon as you enter, the brick walls, the bar area and stand and can lighting will appeal sophistication. We had Westley as server and he was 5 star all the way. They have elaborate wine and liquor selection and they can even make some great mock tails on the fly. It’s cozy atmosphere but very good utilization of space and service is fast. You won’t go wrong with Lobster turnover or Veal dumplings for starters. Entree and A la carte dishes have great choices - if you are going for A la carte dish then a  salad (try the apple salad- it was one of the most delicious part of the meal) or soup and side dish is highly recommended as portion sizes are small - but love the plating! Don’t skip the desert menu and if you are adventurous go for the Espresso martin. Definitely coming here again!!

I visited Sidney Street Cafe on a work trip with 6 colleagues. We sat in the bar at tables and were attentively served by Richard. He is a treasure and provided an unforgettable experience for the group. Wine, food, and cocktails were top-notch. I had the halibut with a side of collard greens and there was not a morsel left.
Had the lobster popovers, tenderloin and a couple desserts. All delicious.  House cocktails were great as well!

properties.adr_address: 4239 Lindell Blvd, St. Louis, MO 63108, USA
properties.formatted_address: 4239 Lindell Blvd, St. Louis, MO 63108, USA
properties.name: Bait

reviews.text: This restaurant is a hidden gem.  I don't often give 5-star reviews, but I couldn't think of anything wrong with our dining experience.   The food is a little pricey, but....the ingredients were all very fresh, were cooked well, and the portions were plentiful.  We both got small plates, main dishes, and drinks, and our bill was still only $110 for 2 people (even with a $39 fish dish and $12 glass of wine).  The apple salad was large enough to be an entree.  The service was fantastic!  Best we've had in a while.  The server was extremely knowledgeable about the wine list and which would pair well with the food.  If you asked where the restroom was, they'd walk you there.  If someone was leaving, they'd open the door for them.  All were masked up as well.  The pace was right.  The music was even perfect for the ambiance.   This is a must-try restaurant!  Do make reservations, though, because they don't have a ton of tables.

This restaurant is such a vibe! We were about an hour early for our reservation and the hostess was very accommodating. Staff was wonderful. They have nice outdoor seating, but I dined inside. Absolutely beautiful, vibey atmosphere with good music. I took my 12 yr old son, so they are kid friendly as well. Food delivered to your table keeping presentation in mind, and it was all delicious!

A fine dining soul seafood experience in landlocked Saint Louis- definitely one of the best for special nights (or a family brunch)- may remind you a bit of NOLA. Thoughtful decoration, amazing always smiling wait staff and a hard working General Manager Mr Thurman makes this place a shining star in CWE neighborhood. Reservation is highly recommend, finding parking on street may be sometime tough so plan accordingly. It took them some time to get us to our table even though we had reservation but once seated our server Aliyah made the experience amazing! Nice selection of craft cocktails, liquors and wine will complement the very creative artistic small plates and main courses. Beside the seafood menu they have very thoughtfully created vegetable dishes such as Carrot three ways, Flash fried Brussels! Duck Rangoon was great - wish it came more than just three in a plate. Some of the popular dishes such as whole fried Caribbean red snapper are a feast for the eye! Main course food portions are huge. Alligator tacos had a spicy touch!! The reason for my 4 star review is that even though we were party of three they had 4 guests listed in our bill and added 20% gratuity with additional suggested tip…so double check the bill-otherwise everything was great and definitely returning back!!

We went here for our 5 year anniversary and it was amazing!!! The food was delicious, the drinks, were perfect and the wine was excellent! Not to mention how sweet, welcoming, and friendly the host was. Our waiter was also so kind and funny. He sang happy birthday to the table next to us and his voice was so good! I would 100% recommend. It is completely worth the price! We felt so welcomed and at home! We definitely will be back. Thanks for such a great experience!!!

Stumbled across this place and glad I did!!

Food: 4.5 stars.  This is high level culinary art!

Service: 4.5 stars!  Delbert is the man!!!

Cleanliness: 4.5 stars!

Overall:  For delicious Southern Food with a twistyou need to eat here!   This is not just a restaurant, it’s an experience!  Thank you to everyone at Bait for such a phenomenal experience and more importantly the passion that is so contagious at your restaurant. From the guy making the drinks to the chef, it’s first class!!

properties.adr_address: 3900 Laclede Ave, St. Louis, MO 63108, USA
properties.formatted_address: 3900 Laclede Ave, St. Louis, MO 63108, USA
properties.name: Saucy Porka Midtown

reviews.text: This place is unique! High flavor food and fast! The look and feel of the place is warm and inviting. Staff is friendly and helpful. The bacos are amazing. Can’t wait to come back!

Visited at noon on a Thursday. Surprisingly there was only one or two customers. Food came out fast. Fries were cold but everything else was fine. The sandwiches and fries were tasty. We tried a pork breakfast sandwich and the 5 spice duck bahnmi.

I was really surprised at how much I liked it! Asian fusion can be so hit-or-miss, but they definitely hit here! The bao was steamed perfectly, the baco filling was delicious, and we subbed sweet potato in for the monkey fries with no regrets. I'll be back to try other menu items.

Food was good and it arrived at our table quickly.   But I did not like that there aren't paper menus, you have to scan the QR code for menu.  Then you order on line,  and tip before your food arrives to your table.  Afterwards you clean your own table.  I tipped $10 for her to bring food to my table.

Saucy porka was a great addition to the central west end!  Reasonably priced, fresh, and tasty dishes.  Food came out fast.  Staff is super friendly and helpful.  The bowls are delicious.  The coffee is AMAZING.   Excited to try the sandwiches next.  So glad this business is investing in this area.

properties.adr_address: 4605 Olive St, St. Louis, MO 63108-1816, USA
properties.formatted_address: 4605 Olive St, St. Louis, MO 63108, USA
properties.name: Bowood by Niche

reviews.text: As soon as you enter the space, it brings calm and joy - great use of pastel color, soft light and chandeliers, water color drawings, paintings and flowers. Some restaurants bring to plate more than just the food, and it is one of them. Great indoor and outdoor space with relaxed atmosphere dining but a perfect place for a date night as well. Our server Lauren was pleasant with a big smile and explained the menu very well. Has great selection of beverage including NA cocktails. Selection of Apps as well as Entree is limited but very unique and earthy to taste. Little Gem, potato fritters came in good shareable size. Halibut was very fresh and one of the best I have in STL. Has a great selection of liquors/desert/espresso to end your meal. Will come back again- have heard good things about the breakfast and brunch!!

What a great dining experience today at Bowood. The food is so inspired and the atmosphere makes it all taste even better. I love breakfast food that is beyond ordinary. Great service and teamwork. I’m obsessed with the pancakes. The egg toast is so satisfying. Don’t hesitate to go and make your palate happy!!

I came here for my anniversary hoping for a romantic evening. The decor is stunning, with half of the space looking like a mysterious forest where I think they sell flowers and greenery. The other half is the restaurant in a monochrome, neutral design. Mostly white with black floors and beige accents.

My girlfriend ordered a pomegranate margarita which she loved. When our food came it out, it was really hit or miss. Our honey nut squash was pretty undercooked. Same with the cauliflower. We were pretty disappointed… yet, they made it it up with the entrees. We got the chicken and steak. The meats were practically perfect, but again the potatoes were undercooked. We loved the sauces, the flavor profiles were masterfully put together by the chef.

Overall, it was really nice, but we were disappointed with half of our food.

Stopped in for dinner as they recently updated the menu. Great service and experience. Food was 4.5 as the appetizers fell a little short of expectations, but desserts (all three) stole the show. Worth the experience and another great restaurant from G Craft and team.

This is a GOOD restaurant in St. Louis. I enjoyed our meal tonight.
The setting is casual and beautiful, you can dress up if you like but you won’t be intimidated if you don’t.

I like their weekly change prix fixe menu, I think it means they use seasonal ingredients and the chef is creative & playful.

They cook EVERY ingredient to the perfect doneness. I like the sauce they created for every dish, just right to make the dish interesting but not overpower the main ingredients. The fish was fantastic to me, normally Restaurants use filets but they choose to present it with whole fish; it was well seasoned and tender. This is the best trout I have in St. Louis.

The desserts are good but I felt a bit heavy.

I hope this restaurant can hold up this quality after its expansion this summer. 🙏 please.

properties.adr_address: 411 N 8th St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.formatted_address: 411 N 8th St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Sauce on the Side

reviews.text: Amazing and large portions. Price was more then fair for how much you get. Their calzone's are twice the size of anything I have had before and they are more then happy to help with custom orders. Everyone was so friendly and helpful. Food was so delicious we will be back.
OMG! Delicious. The aromas told us we were in for a treat before we even sat down. The restaurant had a good feel. The location was very nice as well.

I placed an order via telephone for pick up and it was ready within 10 to 15 minutes. I ordered the "Magic Carpet Ride" which had all types of mushrooms,  cheese,  garlic, and Garlic Honey Oil.

I never thought it a calzone could be so delicious!!! The bread is AMAZING. It's so soft, fresh,  fragrant, and chewy. The honey oil elevated it so much!!! The filling was also amazing. Plenty of it. And the garlic butter to dip it in put it OVER THE TOP.

I was obsessed. I was supposed to save it for my plane ride home but it never even made it to the airport.

If I ever come back to St. Louis, this is it. I won't go anywhere else. I must return. Amazing.

reviews.author_name: Landquist & Son Bifold and Pivot Closet Doors
reviews.text: Make it a point every year to stop at Sauce on the Side. The best calzones, love the selections. The craft beer and seltzer selection is great. Support local.

First let me say, I really love this restaurant but a great deal of how your treated determines if you’ll return. Me and my husband visited this sauce on the side down town around 7:15 pm on 3/23. They messed our order up while we were in the mist of going out of town so we had to get a rain check. The next time we go to redeem our meal which they only replaced one calzone because they couldn’t find they order replacement book. The caller was rude and asked did we call back after the order was messed up again, not only did we call we kept them. The label didn’t match what should’ve been in the box. The rudest person I’ve ever met in a customer service environment. I will not return here and won’t recommend. The  Calzone was half done and very greasy. Very displeased

properties.adr_address: 710 N 2nd St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Low-key spot on historic Laclede's Landing for beer, burgers, pizza & such, plus TV sports.

properties.formatted_address: 710 N 2nd St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: The Lou Eats & Drinks

reviews.text: Fun place. Good food. We had smash burgers and Caesar salad - both very good. Good happy hour and shot-drinking challenge that makes for a party atmosphere. Friendly fast service.

I love this place! Fast and amazing service. Friendly staff, great selection of drinks, and tasty food! The Lou Melt or the Sweet and Spicy wings are everything! Not to mention 124 shot board!!! Fun environment, always a great experience!

It was ok ,good music,nice vibes,stumbled up on this place looking for another..but I must say,no cover charge but they are Taxing in there, 20%automatic gratuity on errrthing...you heard,and they are very slow on food orders but it was good,had cheeseburger and tots..seasoned very well.

My server Steph was funny friendly and well informed. I had two St.Louis staples. TOASTED RAVIOLI AND GOOEY BUTTER CAKE along with a local brew INCARNATION IPA. Everything was delicious. I will be back next time I'm in town.

Nice bar with a patio, they're really running with their shot board idea but plenty of other options. Has a dive feel which I love but seemed a little expensive for the vibe.
Unfortunately its one of the last bars left in Lacledes Landing. Wish it was still a happening area!

properties.adr_address: 811 Spruce St, St. Louis, MO 63102-1717, USA

editorial_summary.overview: An open kitchen serves upscale New American fare in a modern, loftlike setting at the Westin.

properties.formatted_address: 811 Spruce St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: Quattro Trattoria + Pizzeria

reviews.text:
My brother and I were downtown for the 2023 Cardinals home opener. We hit the pep rally in Ballpark Village and then hit Quattro for lunch before the gates opened at the stadium.
We sat at the bar.  The place was busy, but not packed.  The service was just a tad slow, (because they were busy) but attentive.
We both had burgers and fries, and great conversations with other Cardinals fans from elsewhere who were there for the same reasons.
My burger was cooked to perfection the way I wanted it.  The fries were generous and quite enough, and quite delicious.
Having lunch here was a very nice highlight of my whole experience of attending my first Cardinals home opener.
I certainly would like to visit your establishment again.

A Solid Hotel Restaurant for a Quick and Convenient Bite.

I was staying at the Westin for a business trip, waiting for my room to be ready and it was close enough to lunch. I started off with the Toasted Ravioli ($8) with marinara sauce and it came out quick. It was sprinkled with parmesan cheese and tasted good. My only recommendation would be to cook them for one minute less, so they do not come out softer.

I also ordered the Pollo Panini ($14), a grilled chicken breast, with baby spinach, heirloom tomato, fontina, and pesto. The sandwich was solid, good taste, and could have used more pesto. However, the side... a fennel and orange slaw, was tremendous! Never had anything like it and I thoroughly enjoyed it. I would have ordered a couple more sides!

Overall, this was a good restaurant that served its purpose, coupled to a hotel. You can come down for a convenient, good meal for lunch or dinner.
It was great pizza for a hotel. The mozzarella pizza with tomatoes was my favorite. My whole family really enjoyed it!

Just had one of the worst brunch experiences ever at Quattro. It took about an hour to get served subpar food. My $4 coffee was never refilled, had to ask twice to have water refilled, and even asked to have our order canceled since it was taking so long. Once we asked to cancel, they quickly started making the order (you can see the cooks from the table). When my wife asked about my daughter’s Cheerios, the waitress rolled her eyes at her. Then I noticed the bill had a 25% gratuity added to it. I would recommend going somewhere else if you’re staying at the Westin. Not the type of food or service I expected. This restaurant has really gone downhill.

This was a happy accident on our night in St. Louis. We stumbled across this restaurant while on a family trip and it was a wonderful experience. The bartender made a perfect martini, they took special requests for food and had prompt attentive service. What we thought was going to be a regular hotel restaurant meal turned out to be excellent!!

properties.adr_address: 7036 Clayton Ave, St. Louis, MO 63117, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Stylish American-Italian restaurant for wood-fired pizzas & house-made pastas, plus wines & beers.

properties.formatted_address: 7036 Clayton Ave, St. Louis, MO 63117, USA
properties.name: Basso

reviews.text: This place is downright amazing! The atmosphere gives off heavy date-night vibes as soon as you come down the stairs. The food was top-tier, and they have some really inventive selections. The wild mushroom pizza was one of the best wood-fired pizzas I’ve had. The duck egg on top really took it to the next level. The bucatini was legitimately one of the best pasta dishes I’ve ever had. The calamari was amazing, and don’t sleep on the fries. They also had their own Private Select Four Roses single barrel, and make a delicious old fashioned. I can only give 5 stars, but I would like to give more.

Fantastic atmosphere! Definitely need a reservation at this place. We went on a Wednesday, and it was completely packed. You go down a staircase to get to the restaurant.  They have nice ambiance with flame sconces along the walls.  The salad is large enough for 3 people to share as a starter.

Update: We went back for a second go at Basso and had a much better experience. Service was attentive (shout out Alec!) and fun, the food was delicious and came out quickly after ordering each dish. Thanks for the fun night out, we'll definitely be back.

My man took me here for Valentine’s Day this year, and everything was delicious!! We tried the crispy meatballs, risotto, Basso burger, and tiramisu. The meatballs were very crispy and so delicious. Burger had a nice flavor from the grill and was cooked perfectly. The risotto so creamy and flavorful! I wasn’t super impressed with the tiramisu coffee flavoring,  but it was very creamy and smooth. I would recommend to anyone, as long as you aren’t too worried about the pricing.

must commend the restaurant
It’s located down a flight of stairs and the lighting is on the darker side but….
Amazing food ! great service Maria. Thank you
The chef Cody deserves applause for the great fare served to us
We had roasted cauliflower 5/5
whipped mascarpone 5/5’
Margherita pizza 5/5
Mushroom and Truffle Pizza 5/5
Casa Insalata 5/5 great salad chef
Pippardelle Pasta again 5/5
Cacio E pepe paled in comparison
followed by dessert
Tiramisu 4/5
Gelatos 3/5

properties.adr_address: 1911 Locust St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Sleek nightspot in airy, modern digs with a full bar, lots of video screens & inventive pub grub.

properties.formatted_address: 1911 Locust St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: The Marquee Restaurant & Lounge

reviews.text: Loved the Brunch After Dark!! The vibe, the music, everything was very decent.. drinks were also on point! I will gladly go back and experience another evening here. My only complaint is that my friend believes she accidentally left her credit card inside the bill booklet. She tried to call the listed number a few times and couldn't reach a live person, only a voicemail. Definitely should have a number to reach someone at all times during open business hours, given that they're open til 3am. However, that's not enough to keep me from going back for another fun night at this great spot.

Went for brunch and it was delicious. Sometimes the food is hit or miss but every time it’s at least edible. Service is fair…may need to hire more people to help service such a large brunch crowd. Drinks are ok

We really enjoyed the experience. Came in town for the weekend to celebrate my wife’s birthday.  Showed up for the Saturday Brunch and the vibe and food was awesome.  Our server Natalie was on point and very attentive.  She even gave us some recommendations of places to try while we were in town.  Love to support black businesses and we will definitely be back when we’re in the area.

It was my bday weekend and we were the first in the building and the last to eat. We were a party of 6 and out of 6 orders, the appetizers were the only thing good. 3 orders had to be returned because they were cold.  The service wasn't too bad. The shrimp tacos were fire 🔥

Really nice brunch, food was delicious and with a nice presentation. The restaurant was well staffed and wait staff was attentive. They had a DJ playing a nice mix of current and throw back music (had everyone nodding their heads to the beat while eating). Over all a great experience, very nice concept, and somewhere I will go back in the future.

properties.adr_address: 3307 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Cozy option with an open kitchen preparing creative local dishes from a tasting menu, plus wine.

properties.formatted_address: 3307 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Bulrush StL Restaurant

reviews.text:
We love food based experiences and Bulrush did not disappoint. The owner/chef explains the sustainability and research behind the concept as you progress, you learn about the waste control processes and how the people of the Ozarks lived in the past. You got these stories through the food Bulrush makes for you. Definitely a fun and tasty way to learn about food, history and possibilities for the future.

The welcome drinks, palate cleanser was a nice segue Into the space. We did the pairing option and wish we had not ordered a starter cocktail. Other than that small change, we had a fantastic experience!

I think the best way to describe our experience would be revolutionary. The food was absolutely delicious. Each dish is thoughtfully researched and crafted using sustainable methods. I have seen reviews that state that this place is a once a year treat, but I absolutely disagree. We will be going here as often as we are able. This is way all restaurants should be operated, with a strong emphasis on incredible tasting food, local sustainability and education.

My partner and I went here for the first time for my birthday and we were completely blown away! I'm a vegetarian and never once felt like my dietary needs were an afterthought. Every dish that had veggie modifications was prepared with just as much care and attention as the meat dishes. Each dish was more impressive than the last, and I was so sad when the last dish was served. I didn't want to leave! Chef Rob and his team are wonderful, hospitable individuals and we thoroughly enjoyed the educational components of the evening. This was not a meal, it was an EXPERIENCE. I would give Bulrush six stars if I could!

This was a magical experience and we enjoyed every second of it (we have been to several Michelin restaurants and this one should be one of them!). Food was phenomenal, service flawless, Chef Rob passionate about food, local ingredients and community. As a scientist I was very interested to hear about their seed and wine research. We also enjoyed company of people dining with us! We will be back!

Amazing intimate chef's tasting menu that uses zero waste practices. We added on the drink package and it was well worth the prices as we received 3 wine pours and 2 cocktail pairings. My only complaint would be that it would be nice to add a coffee or a dessert wine with the last course

properties.adr_address: 705 Olive St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Retro-chic restaurant in the Hotel Saint Louis serving comfort food with a twist, plus cocktails.

properties.formatted_address: 705 Olive St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Union 30

reviews.text:
TLDR; get cocktails. The "Chilean Seabass" is probably cod.

I read the reviews of this place, and I wish I'd listened, but we ate here because we were staying in the hotel. The bartenders were friendly and skilled--the cocktails were excellent, yet overpriced. I had a Bulleit Old Fashioned that was $19. I'd do it again, but with a different bourbon next time. For my meal, I ordered the Chilean seabass. I've had it many times, and I know what to expect in terms of texture and taste. Honestly, I think the fish I was served was cod because the texture of the fish was wrong--it was firm like cod, not soft and flaky like Chilean seabass. The entrée was also really oily.  I definitely plan to go back to the hotel and have drinks at the bar (with less expensive bourbon), but I don't plan to eat there ever again.
Food was good. Drinks were great. Service was slow. I would definitely go back again. They have one vegan option in the dinner menu. But it works for groups with different eating habits.
I loved eating here! It was such a fun experience. My server was so sweet and the duck confit flatbread and it was so good with the goat cheese. I

The servers were very attentive ad the food came in a timely fashion. The plates were presented nicely and the food was delicious! Everyone made sure that I had a positive experience! I recommend getting dessert because every cake, pie, and ice cream was outstanding!

Avoid.  No host but sign says wait for seating.  Service was fine but a long wait for food when there was only one other table.  Prices are higher than what google shows and my halibut was $48 when the restaurant menu showed $38.  Halibut was cooked well but was placed on a sopping pile of beets and beets juice.  Had to scrap away the beets to save the halibut.  French soup was ok and nothing to advertise as a signature dish.  Overall food was bland and not worth $100 for one person.

properties.adr_address: 820 Olive St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.formatted_address: 820 Olive St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Dao Tien - Downtown

reviews.text: Wow! First time in St. Louis and I think I may have found my favorite Vietnamese restaurant here! Great ambiance! The pho was the PERFECT level of spice (I like it hot). The coffee was also phenomenal. Most importantly, exceptional customer service! Hands down the best! You won't be disappointed!

Glad to have checked out their new location!  I've gone to their U.City location a few times in the past, which is now closed.  Their menu brings many choices, quality, and deliciousness all around.  Their new location is beautiful, airy, & spacious!!!  It's definitely worth driving the distance to.  Will definitely go back to again and again.  Thankful to have met the owners as well. :)

I had the lunch special with chicken curry, it was delicious!
The price was great!
I would've loved to continue tasting their menu but I was only in town for work.

Totally recommended!

Great service and quick!
We were looking something to eat. About to go somewhere else and we spot this location. And it did not disappoint! Best food in town
Best eatery in downtown. The place itself is very clean beautiful. The employees are so nice and helpful as well. I’ll def be back for sure 🫶🏻

properties.adr_address: 1327 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Sleek Mediterranean joint serving grab-&-go wraps, salads & rice bowls in airy, comfortable digs.

properties.formatted_address: 1327 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Medina Grill

reviews.text: Good food and great service. They were very welcoming and made some good recommendations. We had shwarma salads and they were delicious. The meat was extremely tender and seasoned great. First time in St. Louis and will definitely be back next time I'm in town!

Found this place from a gluten free app and it did not disappoint. I got a spicy chicken rice bowl that was delicious. I felt a little gluten sick afterwards  but it went away fast so might just be a new food introduced to the body. Highly recommend.
