Food was wonderful and the staff was great! Since we were knew to the restaurant, one of the staff took time to walk us through the menu and answer any questions we had. I ordered the Medina rice bowl and it was amazing. Their tzaziki sauce was mellow and refreshing. There wasn't an overpowering flavor of dill or cucumber.
Amazing food. Full of flavor the staff was so nice with helping us pick out items to try. That desserts were also very good!

Wow!! I can’t recommend this place enough. I brought 20 junior high and high school students from rural KS to St. Louis. I wanted them to try some new food while here for the City Museum. We stopped here and were not only served spectacular food, but received phenomenal service as well. They were quick, organized, clean, kind, and the food was even better.

properties.adr_address: 1831 Sidney St, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Rustic eatery with fishermen photos & retro accents offering lobster, po' boys, shrimp & a raw bar.

properties.formatted_address: 1831 Sidney St, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA
properties.name: Peacemaker Lobster & Crab

reviews.text: Nice Nice Nice! The food was good! Lobster Roll and Cold Lime Crab sandwiches. The fries are amazing. You think there just like any other fries. Nope! Seasoned good! The bread was crisp and buttery but soft on the inside to perfection. I could have passed on the homemade chips and dip but I was really hungry do I wanted to get at it! The drinks were pretty good and unique. I will go again and try there other menu items. Of course with the fries. The atmosphere was clean. Bathroom was clean. Very nice Benton Park view.

Park your car on the street and take a stroll to this upscale but casual dining space. No reservations accepted but it has ample indoor and great patio space as well as bar seating area to enjoy some fresh lobster, cram, oysters etc. Servers are excellent and service is pretty fast. We got some raw Oysters from Massachusetts as starters and it was excellent. Lot of other choices of Poor boy shrimp, crawfish etc sandwiches as well as Crab rolls etc. Wine list by the glass or bottle is good and some great cocktail choices are there to enjoy. If you still have room then end your meal with some home made shareable desserts/pies. An excellent experience overall and one of the top recommended restaurants dirty your hand!!

Upscale seafood dining just south of the downtown arch. The dress was casual attire but the food was above board excellent. Our server Nate was patient and answered our questions throughly with each course. We took 90 minutes to enjoy several selections. We were never rushed. You should expect to more for a wonderful meal like this, however it was worth the price. I give my top recommendation.

Looking for the best seafood in the city? You have to try Peacemaker! This eatery is tucked into the historic Benton Park neighborhood, offering high quality, fresh seafood at its finest.

We ordered the Lobster Roll (Connecticut style); served on a warm, buttery bun with delicious pieces of tender lobster and chips on the side. The Shrimp Boil is a feast on its’ own! This plate is served with a generous amount of shrimp, steamed potatoes, corn and a house-made biscuit. The seafood boils are enough for two! The raw oysters and peel & eat shrimp are a must try, as well.

Peacemaker is a little on the expensive side, but entirely worth it. The service is exceptional and the team offers great recommendations. The cocktails are crafted with great ingredients and the atmosphere is warm and inviting. If you haven’t stopped by Peacemaker, you are missing out!

Save your money so you can go here once a day lol…The lobster rolls are phenomenal! Nice amount of lobster, great toast on the bun, and not too much butter. The side of chips were nice and seasoned with a good hint of spice. The shrimp po boy tasted fresh and came hot. The lobster Mac and cheese could use some work. Noodles need about one minute more to cook and the cheese sauce needs to be thickened up to give it that unctuous feel. The drinks were quite tasty and strong like I like it. Definitely will be back over and over

properties.adr_address: 201 S 18th St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Large, stylish spot at the St. Louis Union Station Hotel for modern American fare & craft cocktails.

properties.formatted_address: 201 S 18th St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: The Train Shed at Union Station

reviews.text: This place is spectacular.  It was beautifully decorated! We started with the stuffed tots, and that fried Mac n Cheese.  Both were really good but the fried Mac n Cheese was phenomenal.  We had the BBQ pork steak as an entree and it was perfectly cooked.  It was fork tender, and the BBQ was great.

The atmosphere and motif were both excellent and on point.  Every employee was welcoming and friendly.  I noticed after a patron cleared their table someone was ready to clear the table and disinfect tables and chairs!

I ordered the country fried chicken.  It was tender and delicious.  The mashed potatoes were thick and buttery. The carrots however didn't have any flavor to them.

Overall the food,  the staff,  the service the decor were all excellent and wonderful.

My daughter and I ate here after leaving the aquarium. It was a busy day for the aquarium so naturally the restaurant was a little busy. We put our name on the waitlist and were told it will be a 25 minute wait but it really took only 16 minutes for us to be seated. The wait staff were very busy. We needed refills and it took a while for our waitress to reappear so we could ask her for some.

I originally ordered a lemonade to drink and it tasted like lemon flavored water. I ended up switching it for a sprite. Maybe the syrup was low. I didn’t investigate it, so don’t be afraid to try it for yourself. I saw a child drinking it with no problems.

Our food was delicious. We had the Smash burger (it comes with seasoned waffle fries) and a chicken fried steak meal (it came with mashed potatoes & carrots). I would come back for the burger & fries for sure. My teenager (a young lady of few words) said her meal was good and was looking forward to eating her leftovers for dinner. Not Pictured: We also ordered a Gooey Butter cake to-go. It was just okay. Not like any other one we had before. It tasted like maybe it had too much extract flavor. It wasn’t nasty but it wasn’t for me.

Recap: I’ll be back for sure. There were several appetizers we want to try. The menu has something for everyone. Our bill was $60 for the 2 meals, 2 drinks, and 1 dessert.

My first time here and I decided to go with the Toasted Ravioli, country fried steak with carrots and mashed potatoes. The food was excellent and the decor was amazingly set up. I’m not sure if it was because around New Year or not. The customer service was excellent/attentive we didn’t have to wait for seating. Prices were in between expensive and inexpensive depending on your budget. Very nice place for someone also new to the area. Enjoy :)

I had a wonderful two hour lunch at the Train Shed during the busy holiday season and loved every moment of it. From the warm greeting by the hostess to the great food and amazing waitstaff... it was what all restaurant experiences should be. While the place is fairly upscale in appearance my family, including my 4 year old, were very welcomed here. We had a great time and I highly recommend it!

properties.adr_address: 1 Fine Arts Dr, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Stylish modern eatery at the Saint Louis Art Museum serving seasonal New American cuisine.

properties.formatted_address: 1 Fine Arts Dr, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA
properties.name: Panorama Restaurant

reviews.text: We originally went on our stay cation honeymoon 7 years ago so it's special to us. We also had our first date and got engaged in the SLAM so its special for us. We come back whenever we can. So glad to see it reopened after 2 long years.  The food was delicious(seasoned perfectly),but we were disappointed they didn't do brunch anymore. Also there was nowhere in the reservation to put it was our anniversary so there wasn't anything special like past years.
Great little hidden gem in the art museum. Food was fresh and delicious and the service was great. I really enjoyed the mimosa cocktail as well.

The Panorama has a very lovely view. The food is spectacular, though the steak portion size could be a bit bigger. The desert is delectable. And the staff works like a well oiled machine. I love dining here.
Each of us tried a different menu item. We were so very impressed with the food and our host was on top of it! He quickly filled our beverages when they were low. EXCELLENT!

Conveniently located at the eaat entrance of SLAM. My friends & I made reservations with enough time to explore the amazing Kehinde Wiley & Graphic Revolution exhibits today.

Brandy was an ok server; nothing to complain about nor write home. It was pretty straight to the point (order, deliver, check).

We all drink lol...so Chardonnay & Rosé domed the table. I opted for the Grilled Eggplant entree. A lovely tower of perfectly grilled thick sliced eggplant,  forest mushrooms, quinoa, sweet red peppers, goat cheese & basil mint oil. It was delicious. My dining companions ordered the Quiche of the day & Ceasar salad. Both were pleased with presentation & taste.

The dining room is spacious, open & offers a wonderful view overlooking Forest Park's Art Hill.  Fresh roses, heavy silverware & linen napkins were the place setting. Coat check, hostess stand, covered parking are available for those wondering.

properties.adr_address: 3257 Ivanhoe Ave, St. Louis, MO 63139-2245, USA
properties.formatted_address: 3257 Ivanhoe Ave, St. Louis, MO 63139, USA
properties.name: Farmhaus Restaurant

reviews.text: My husband and I both had the chef’s prefixe for his birthday dinner this evening; he enjoyed the wine pairings. We thought the three plates were very good, red snapper being most exceptional. Our server was such a sweet girl, and all staff were so kind and enthusiastic! Plates were coursed out appropriately time-wise.

Went for my second time: deliciously beautiful and amazing service! I got the pre-fixe meal which had butternut squash pasta, scallops over a parsnip purée, and a tender, juicy pork over sweet potatoes and turnips. Cant wait to come here another time!

Yet another stop on the STL Top 100 2022, and another that has failed to disappoint!  We made a reservation via phone a few days before, and had no problem getting in.  The bar area has a handful of tables as well as bar seating.  The main dining area has a few more tables, and the decor is quite spartan.  I'd expected a bit more ambiance, but it wasn't awful.

Farmhaus is no kidding farm to table, yet the prices are still more than reasonable.  The summer salad was very well balanced, consisting of an array of flavors.  The ribeye was massive, perfectly cooked, and full of flavor; the green beans and mashed sweet/russet potatoes were perfection as well.  The red snapper and polenta was good, but didn't have the same 'wow' (or price) factor as the ribeye.

This place has been on the Top 100 for at least a couple years, and it's no wonder why.

Absolutely AMAZING! Such sweet service, with genuinely nice people. Food was stunning, words cannot express the delicious meal we just had. I highly recommend getting the Butternut Squash Agnolotti and Pierogies!

(PS: Having a couple of glasses, ordering 4 meals, and dessert; the check was much lower than expected from the phenomenal meal)
An excellent restaurant led by James Beard nominee for best chef in the Midwest region, Kevin Willmann. Small plates and entrees curated on a daily, evolving menu.

properties.adr_address: 1923 Park Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104-2536, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Seasonal small plates, mains & cocktails are served in a warm, stylish setting.

properties.formatted_address: 1923 Park Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA
properties.name: Polite Society Restaurant and Bar

reviews.text: First time at this establishment! Classic Eggs Benedict was perfect and the cook did not get anything wrong! Good vibes this morning. Wait staff perfectly behaved and Lisa R. was friendly pleasant and accommodating. Service was prompt and professional. Not too rushed as I was there just after they opened for brunch (9 am Sundays). I am certain that this establishment gets very busy! I will have to rate them during such time that I return either by myself or with company. I will definitely return!

Had a great brunch experience here! Everyone in my party enjoyed their food. I ordered a pretty basic Belgian waffle but did sample around the table and  the Chorizo Avocado Benedict and Brunch Monster (pictured) were both delicious. Unlimited mimosas were def a factor in picking this place, and they DID not disappoint. Although there is a hour and thirty minute limit, they pour a great mix that isn't too heavy on the OJ🤗. Food and mimosas were on point and the atmosphere was cute and quaint. I would definitely visit again if I am in St. Louis and recommend anyone to give it a try if looking for a brunch spot with unlimited mimosas!😜

First time at Polite Society for brunch and it did not disappoint! Chicken & waffles were the absolute best I've ever tasted & the cherry on tip was the Thai chili maple syrup, OMG!  Shrimp & grits were spectacular and I'm not a fan of grits in general,  but these were lucky the bowl clean delicious!!
I've also gone fur Dinner and the spinach dip was soon good, as well as a wonderful burger, so delicious.  My cocktail, the Michigander, was a joy to sip. If you like bourbon, don't sleep on that one!

We are so full and so happy! The food was amazing. Everything looked good so my husband and I got 4 appetizers, drinks, and dessert. I don't have anything negative to say, because the dining experience overall was great. Eric the waiter was professional, the ambience was classy, the tables were socially distanced, and we loved how accommodating everyone was. We intend to return.

We were visiting St. Louis on a business trip and we always like to find local eateries to enjoy when we travel.

Polite Society was an excellent experience!!! Reservations are recommended!! It's a cozy and intimate atmosphere, which does make it loud but it is cozy. The food was incredible, every crumb! You could tell the chef put a lot of heart and thought into his flavors and menus. There were also gluten-free options on the menu, which was one of our reasons for choosing them. The staff was friendly and welcoming. We highly recommend dinner at Polite Society!

properties.adr_address: 799 Clark Ave, St. Louis, MO 63102-1714, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Polished destination with an open kitchen serving seafood & steak, plus cocktails & whiskey.

properties.formatted_address: 799 Clark Ave, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: Clark & Bourbon

reviews.text: Classy place inside a hotel. Exceptional service. Crab cakes are more crab than cake, which is what you like to see. Steaks are excellent. Oysters vary depending on source. Ballpark village needed a place like this. I would definitely go back. The bar was quiet, which is a nice change of pace if you need some respite from noisy bars and want to have conversation.

I absolutely loved the food. Everything tasted great. My only complaint would be the temperature of the food and I think that's because my waitress was not attentive to the few tables she had. However the manager did step in a couple of times and that was very awesome.

A very yummy hotel restaurant. I have a really cool gas fireplace in there high top tables, low top tables they got a little couch section because it is part of a hotel. The bartenders are really great. The cocktails are mixed wonderfully, and the food is also very good. We got the tuna tartare, a charcuterie, board, some french fries, and a couple other items to share, and they were all very yummy.

This place definitely does give more upscale fives and the price is sort of reflect that but it is a nice hotel and makes you feel kind of fancy!

You gotta check this place out for dinner sometime never really cool patio to that's right across the street from Busch Stadium so it might be a good place to pregame a baseball match.

Great little place with awesome team members who are friendly and professional. Each section inside this hotel restaurant is picture perfect! I got the ribeye sandwich and I absolutely loved it! The flavors are perfect and the bread is delicious! This is a great spot for good food and pics!

I attend Cardinals baseball games all the time, but this is the first time I stopped here for lunch.  Very bright and open.  Love the option to sit outside.  Staff was friendly and professional.  Food prices were very high.  The food tasted ok. Amazing selection of whiskey and bourbon.  Great place to bring some friends for drinks.

properties.adr_address: 1603 McCausland Ave, St. Louis, MO 63117, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Mediterranean & New American small plates & entrees served in upscale, sophisticated surrounds.

properties.formatted_address: 1603 McCausland Ave, St. Louis, MO 63117, USA
properties.name: Pan D'Olive

reviews.text: It’s an absolute surprise! I love every dish there. The price is also very reasonable for their quality! I highly recommend feta stick and seafood pasta. The shrimp scampi is the biggest prize. Pairing with risotto is unusual but works perfectly.

Wowza! I drive past here all the time and boy am I glad I stopped for dinner. The recommended wine was lovely and the food was magnificent. I ordered the medallions and it was some of the best food I have had in a while. I was hesitant based on the description, didn’t know what to expect, and it blew me away. Great quality food and drink plus great service - will be back again

Such a lovely place for lunch. Elegant, quiet, understated. Great service, delicious Mediterranean food! 😋 Felt comfortable in my black jeans and sweater, but some folks with skirts/ties - probably business lunch. Two ate for $40 tax and tip.
Their happy hour is awesome! It's such a great deal for food and drinks and everything was good. We ordered most of the menu - 2 flatbread, hummus, arancini, phyllo cigars and the dessert platter.
So good, my now favorite place to eat at! The server and owner were so kind and attentive. 10/10 experience. We got the steak and a spicy pasta, I recommend!

properties.adr_address: 6335 Clayton Ave, St. Louis, MO 63139-3209, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Gastropub offering elevated American plates, craft beer & cocktails in a warm, polished atmosphere.

properties.formatted_address: 6335 Clayton Ave, St. Louis, MO 63139, USA
properties.name: Stone Turtle Restaurant and Bar

reviews.text: Stone turtle was an extremely wonderful find within walking distance of the St Louis zoo.  The tiger rolls were perfect, and the wild caught bass was seasoned wonderfully. The drinks were fun and the socialista offered several layers of great flavor. Dessert was decadent as it should be. This was definitely one of the best dining spots we've been to in a year. Do make a reservation and definitely stop in.

The waitress was very knowledgeable and nice. The calamari was delicious and the drinks. The salmon, potatoes, and broccoli wasn’t the best. My husband liked his steak, but overall don’t think we will visit again.

I stumbled across this restaurant on Google search. I viewed the menu and some of the food items and thought, "this is my type of restaurant." And to my surprise, it was... the Tiger Roll with the cilantro jam was EVERYTHING‼️😋 the grapefruit was delicious and the Libations were great as well. The only thing I think needs to be revamped is the chicken and waffles. I get that they may have been going for a Southern Chicken and Waffle feel where the crust looks almost burned but the chicken is Juicy on the inside... but it was definitely not that experience. After sending it back and getting the replaced order it was still not tasty. It was dry and overcooked each time the crust was way too crispy and beef jerky chewy. The waffle needs a little bit more weight to it, it was as if I was eating the air.. it was too lightweight and crispy. Other than that, I will definitely go back.

The service was superb. The food was very tasty while the drinks where strong. The old fashioned has a turtle in ice to be a souvenir haha. The pork was very tasty although I wasn’t into the Brussels sprouts that were served. But that would be my only complaint,
Great location near the Zoo in Dogtown.  The Brisket dip was excellent.  It is way too much food. Excellent French fries.  The drinks were unique and tasty. The omelets are great to, try either.

properties.adr_address: 999 N 2nd St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA

editorial_summary.overview: A menu specializing in South American-inspired dishes & cocktails in a contemporary dining room.

properties.formatted_address: 999 N 2nd St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: Cinder House and Bar

reviews.text: Such a fun atmosphere. The rooftop is the best in St. Louis. The views and vibes are unmatched. The food is delicious. The drinks were very refreshing. Definitely pricey, but worth it. If you are looking for a fun date night, girls night out, or even just happy hour, this is a great option. I recommend this place to some of my out of town guests as well!

Had an amazing evening at Cinder House and Bar tonight for an anniversary date. Such an amazing view of the city when you look out the windows. Aside from the breathtaking view, the food was above and beyond all expectations. So much attention to detail and finesse went in to each and every plate. To top everything off, the level of hospitality that Cinder House provides truly is something that all restaurants should strive for. Top notch on all levels. Highly recommended.

Nice all the way around! Great decor, great view, great service, and great food! The French Toast was nice and thick had a cakey type of taste. The avocado toast was a nice size for me. It was fresh and flavorful. Candied pecans added a nice crunch and sweetness. I will say that I wish the toast itself had more flavor I ate the top off the bread and left the bread there. The drink was nice and refreshing. I have to check out their dinner now

Service was great (though they sat us out in the waiting area, away from the dining room. felt it was a little unusual) Cocktail program was fantastic. Food was good, though some dishes felt a bit lacking in depth of flavor. Especially having tried Chef Craft's other concepts. All in all good experience, though I felt it wasn't quite worth the check price.

The food was so amazing and the presentation was well worth the price. The food taste just as great as the pictures look. Outstanding service. 20% gratuity is included in the price. Our reservation was stunning. There was a small band playing music right outside the eatery next to the entrance. Nice experience.

properties.adr_address: 4200 Manchester Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Casual, family-owned fixture with an old-world vibe, homemade Middle Eastern meals & Turkish coffee.

properties.formatted_address: 4200 Manchester Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA
properties.name: Sultan Mediterranean Restaurant

reviews.text: Ate here for the first time this past Sunday. We got there around 5:30 and it was packed.   My kids and I love Mediterranean food and this place is our new favorite.  The food came out of the kitchen piping hot and was delicious!  In fact, Everything on the menu sounded so good it was hard to decide what to order.  They also have a nice vegetarian menu.  I can’t wait to go back and try something new!

As a big fan of Mediterranean foodie, I want to give a try when I m visiting St Louis. I like the decorations inside of the restaurant. It is a great restaurant if you have not had any middle eastern food before. I wish appetizer size could be smaller or even have combo( three or four in one plant) then I could have more taste with the bread. Nana bread is delicious! PS, lemonade with mint( I guess the mint is not fresh mint. Maybe it's dry mint) is nice.

Food was very good, I just wish I was a bit more hungry as I felt quite full after the appetizers. The felafel with hummus was probably my favorite, but we also had some delicious tabule. For entrees we got a few of the vegetarian options which were also good and the portions were very large. The service was good, and the atmosphere was nice, it did feel a little dark, a couple more lights would be nice. I would definitely recommend this place!

Stopped by to have a solo afternoon lunch. It was pretty empty when I arrived, but was greeted as soon as I walked in. My server was very kind and made a REALLY good recommendation since I wasn’t sure what to order. The food was absolutely delicious. Very flavorful and the naan bread was fresh out of the oven. I will be back.

Chic Mediterranean joint. Quite busy with lack of workers. So even tough there are quite a few empty tables, be prepared to wait. The place is mostly family owned with relatives waiting at tables. The people who interfaced with us were surprisingly very rude. They made us wait a long time and sit at a table we didn't want and then while ordering straight up told us they don't have majority of the menu. No apology or courtesy. The food came quickly and well made. Hummus was given extremely less quantity. Falafel were fine. Curries were very similar in taste. Taste was good though. Non veg pulao was really good. Veg pulao was tasteless. Wings were a joke. You better wings in street fairs. Overall the food was decent enough, and well presented, so giving it 4 stars. Next time i would rather take out than sit and eat. Not a good experience for dining.

properties.adr_address: 2501 S Jefferson Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Chic spot with a cocktail bar, dishing up creative dishes made from locally sourced ingredients.

properties.formatted_address: 2501 S Jefferson Ave, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA
properties.name: The Lucky Accomplice

reviews.text: Loved the vibe as soon as we walked in. We were a bit sticker shocked of the prices on the menu but once we took a sip of our cocktails we knew they were worth it. The cocktails were some of the best we've ever had. The food that followed did not disappoint either. Flavor and textures of each ingredient were phenomenal. The wait staff was also super friendly and happy to provide recommendations. Highly recommend and definitely worth the higher price point.

We went there for our anniversary. They welcomed us with champagne and it was great celebrating our anniversary with great food and drinks.
The atmosphere was great, food was delicious and cocktails were awesome. Definitely recommend this place.

My husband and I went here while visiting St. Louis for a quick weekend trip and we loved it. It reminded us of a couple of local restaurants in Indianapolis that we also love. It was our anniversary and we noted this on the reservation. We were quickly greeted and seated by a host and our waitress arrived promptly. She was extremely nice and great at explaining dishes and giving recommendations but not overbearing. Two glasses of house champagne (which was great) were brought to our table by a friendly bartender who wished us a Happy Anniversary. Everything we had was divine and I would highly recommend this place if you like creative food and a cool vibe.

This place is a lovely date night spot. It is on the higher side for pricing because of the shared plates style menu. Cocktails around $12-14, shared plates range from $12-34, with a large portion short rib around $80. Service was fantastic, ambience was amazing, food all tasted great. The only complaint is that I wish the scallops came with more than 2 for it's price.

I didn't like the service. The waiter didn't know anything about the menu, just said that everything “so good” 🤦🏻‍♀️
The food was really good, but very small portions. Only two scallops per serving is too small.
The cocktails were amazing.

properties.adr_address: 1500 St Charles St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Swanky parlor offering craft cocktails & inventive New American plates to members & their guests.

properties.formatted_address: 1500 St Charles St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Blood & Sand

reviews.text: Visited for first time for my anniversary. I cannot say enough about this amazing restaurant. Our server Johnathon made us feel welcome and at home from the first moment. He gave us wonderful recommendations, since this was our first visit, and he was right in everyone. We did the five-course experience and every plate was cooked to perfection. I would go back for a full dish of any of them, but also wouldn't want to miss trying something new! I will have a very hard time choosing my next meal at Blood & Sand. Fabulous drinks as well, I love that they are named after song titles. Very lively and fun. We can't wait to visit again.

I went to Blood & Sand for dinner this past weekend with a couple girlfriends and it did not disappoint. The atmosphere, drinks, service, and food were all exceptional. I have never seen kangaroo on a menu before and the chef was fabulous in his preparation. I highly recommend Blood & Sand and I plan on coming back very soon!

My wife and I came here for my Birthday. We had a fantastic time! The food was excellent and the staff was all on point! The lamb was by far my favorite and the wagyu my wife got!

If you’re doing the tasting, I would expect to pay $100+ per person with drinks, etc. They do have all carte as well if you wanted to get only a few and pay less.

However, well worth the experience for a special occasion!

This place is amazing. The servers were all nice, friendly and attentive without interrupting convo. The drinks were perfection. A perfect balance and complimented the meals excellently. If I could dine here every Friday I would!! Delicious food, great atmosphere and great service. Gets all the stars.

From start to finish, we loved our tour through the menu. The 5 course menu with the wine pairing was phenomenal! Cocktails are one of a kind! Exactly what we were looking for during our visit. Blood & Sand has been a highlight of our anniversary vacation here in St Louis!

properties.adr_address: 1 S Broadway, St. Louis, MO 63102-1703, USA
properties.formatted_address: 1 S Broadway, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: Market Street Bistro

reviews.text: I loved their chicken Caesar salad and chicken white chili. Their sandwiches and desserts are good. The only issue I had was that the menu was limited at times due to short staff. Not a big deal, but I feel it is worth mentioning. The staff is great.

Terrible experience. Seated while waiting for our rooms to be finished. Waited about 20 minutes (they were busy) for a drink order/acknowledgement. We ordered drinks and hoped to have 2-3. After we ordered and got our drinks, we waited 45 minutes before we finally left money on the table and left. The waitress stopped at every table around us asking their needs, getting checks, etc., but never once stopped at our table again.

Came in here last night and Genci was behind the bar. The draft beer I ordered was way over priced the menu they had was bland no food items had a description on it. Everything on the menu was way over priced after having Genci become very rude for asking questions about the menu I decided to try the pretzels they had. The pretzel were not pretzel they used numbed shaped pizza dough brushed with butter and no salt and they did not even taste good
Breakfast was pretty good, especially the fruit bar. Worst part was the waiter was in a bad mood and kept muttering under his breath and complaining
Fish tacos were just breaded nothing and dry...service was terrible even the restaurant being empty

properties.formatted_address: 1900 Locust St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Hyde Restaurant & Banquets

reviews.text: Beautiful event space...
Nice venue

properties.adr_address: 1019 Pine St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.formatted_address: 1019 Pine St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Prime 55 Restaurant and Lounge

reviews.text: We found this place just through a Google search. We just needed to eat a good meal and quickly...it had been a long day. The service, food, drinks and atmosphere were all amazing. The salmon was cooked to just the right temperature and the glaze on the lamb chops was delicious. I can't wait to make this a regular place for us to eat.

The wait staff were awesome however, there just isn’t enough space in this restaurant and it looks as if there was only one restroom. There was a continuous flow of traffic and lots of complaints. I did find that the servers were irritated by the line that wrapped through the restaurant from the bathroom line. Also the food is overpriced for the dinner sizes.

I will saw that all of the food was tasty and the general vibe of the restaurant was chill.

Seen the reviews before I came which kinda lowered my expectations but it was good fr, I liked the presentation the person I came withs plate looked fire my steak was okay, I wish they had more cut options than just the one . Overall my favorite part was the carmel crunch cake for dessert that was sum heat . I got it to go but it barely made it home after I tried it at the table. The lighting was terrible tho way too overexposed kinda killed the vibe shining right in my eyes while I’m tryna eat.

ALWAYS good food & good service!
Lobster Mac and cheese, crab cakes, cauliflower steak! All so well seasoned and delicious!
Lamb chops was good.. the vegetables wasn’t edible.. very hard… my first visit.. maybe just a bad night.. also small portions for the price… we loved our waitress thou.

properties.adr_address: 1004 Locust St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Sleek, brick-walled space with serious beer & wine lists plus snacks, charcuterie & larger dishes.

properties.formatted_address: 1004 Locust St, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Bridge Tap House & Wine Bar

reviews.text: What a phenomenal experience! We loved everything about this gorgeous St. Louis gem. The artistic atmosphere, and the food was a work of art too. The flavors were even better than the food looked (and the food was presented with professional precision). Jason gave us a warm welcome and took excellent care of us throughout the meal. We most definitely will be returning and recommending! Bravo!

We recently stopped in to Bridge, and it was a great experience. They have one of the best draft selections in all of downtown. Their mix of beers range in types, ABV and locality. You can order 4oz glasses if you’re into trying several. Their wine selection is also pretty varied, and we enjoyed everything we tried. If you’re hungry make sure to try one of the starters. I recommend the mushroom pâté if they’re currently serving it. Their other entrée dishes have a great blend of flavors. Many of the dishes leveraged flavorful proteins like duck sausage or braised pork belly with savory root veggies and herbs. The ambiance has a refined but rustic feel, and the intimate lighting makes it great for dates or just relaxing with a drink. The bartenders are really friendly and we’re a pleasure to talk to. Prices vary drink-to-drink, but they’re pretty reasonable for downtown.
I highly recommend stopping by if you haven’t, and we plan to make them a pretty regular stop.

first timer...i was treated to a bornDay drink @ this cozy spot on locust st downtown...the blackberry cider was SUPER tasty😋 it was first time assembling a small a la carte charcuterie w smoked gouda, duck sausage😋, focaccia bread, an assortment of nuts & dried fruit and cheddar...cant WAIT to comr back‼️
Great atmosphere and service. Tomato bisque was great. Charcuterie was a build it yourself.   A bit expensive but worth having the ability to sample four (4) meats, a cheese and various other sides.

Outstanding food! Tacos were amazing, salads and charcuterie boards were yummy, great beer selection. Wonderful service by T! Only complaint would be the interior is SO DARK. I'm never a fan of having to use my phone flashlight to read the menu. Also insanely loud, there's a super low ceiling upstairs in the dining area, and the music plus other diners made conversation just at our table of 4 difficult. Still worth it overall, will be back!

properties.adr_address: 3600 Watson Rd, St. Louis, MO 63109-1232, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Renowned venue pairing refined Italian cuisine with classic cocktails & a wine list.

properties.formatted_address: 3600 Watson Rd, St. Louis, MO 63109, USA
properties.name: Trattoria Marcella

reviews.text: Wow! We went here for our engagement dinner and we were blown away with the excellent service from our server Sara B, the incredible food and they included a complimentary vanilla creme brûlée for dessert. It was really amazing! The venue was nicely decorated with a wonderful atmosphere! It was clean and tidy. They were busy, so book a table in advance. You won't regret it. We will return!

Amazing! How I am just hearing about place is beyond me. It definitely competes with other up scale italian restaurants. Plus the bartender/server was a wealth of knowledge, I believe his name was Josh. Go here, you won’t be disappointed.

PHENOMENAL FOOD. OMG!

So I ordered the stuffed chicken spiedini and I couldn’t find a flaw in it if I tried. The chicken was seasoned to perfection. It was nice but perfectly seared. The potatoes flavored well too. The asparagus too. Like I said 10/10 experience.

My date had the lasagna. It was so much food! After eating mine and some of his of course 😉, I was stuffed but happy! The food you can never go wrong with.

Now let’s discuss these drinks. I don’t normally like ordering drinks because they’re too strong but the drinks here were just right! I ended up drinking two and having a merry time! I don’t like to drink because of taste but I wouldn’t hesitate to order a drink here ever! Very pleased!

I’ll try to have room for dessert next time because I definitely need to try it. By the taste of the food I know the dessert won’t disappoint at all.

Great little Italian place right in the heart of the neighborhood. My server Maggie was awesome and knowledgeable. I started off with their fried ravioli and I can say it was the best I have had to date! Most places have cheese but these were filled with meat and it was seasoned so well.  I was able to order off menu and they were gracious enough to make Cacio e pepe for me. It's a simple dish but can be easy to mess up if you don't know what you are doing. It turned out great so I give them extra points for going above to take care of their customers.

The food here is top notch, the wine is excellent. I got the toasted ravioli and it can't with a tomato based sauce.....It was marvelous!!!
There was a bit of a mix up with our order so we had to wait for over an hour but the situation was handled well by the manager and waiter

properties.adr_address: 2340 Market St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.formatted_address: 2340 Market St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: The Bistro – Eat. Drink. Connect.®

reviews.text: Not an expansive menu and no kids menu but the food we got was tasty.  The service was good.  The ice cream shakes were excellent as to be expected.  Definitely no complaints here.  It’s not unreasonably priced for the quality.   We would likely return if we were local.  As traveling through we are glad we stopped.
Food tasted great and staff members were friendly.

The food here was amazing but the service was sub par, The lady behind the counter and helping us was rude and was chewing gum and texting on her phone. She was also putting her hands down her pants and then handling food. We were gonna be scared to eat it but someone else brought it out.
The food is actually pretty decent for a small hotel lobby cafe, and not ridiculously priced.
Egg Frittata was fantastic! Great service and friendly!

properties.adr_address: 925 Geyer Ave #3921, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Buzzy operation serving burritos, tacos & other classics, plus several varieties of margarita.

properties.formatted_address: 925 Geyer Ave #3921, St. Louis, MO 63104, USA
properties.name: Chava's Mexican Restaurant

reviews.author_name: Picture Lady Mrs D Dorenda Townsend
reviews.text: So I’ve been coming here since 2014 and the quality of food & good service never disappoints me. Today, January 3, 2022 After work I needed good fiord and great service & I got it. The best I’ve ever had and you know I eat at plenty of quality restaurants. Hats off to the owner & chef for consistency of food & service during this pandemic. Kathleen was my server tonight and she made great recommendations for their new menu. I love it.

We love this spot in Soulard for fantastic Mexican food! The service was so wonderful tonight - our waitress was so kind and helpful. We honestly didn’t have to ask once for a refill on chips and salsa and they made us feel so comfortable and kept us filled! The chips and salsa here are sooo good - the salsa is a bit on the spicier side but I love that!
We got the El Mireko and Fajitas Rancheros - both were delicious, 100% would get the El Mireko again! The chicken on the Fajitas was really good, had a nice char too - we just weren’t expecting it to be so soupy but the stew (?) it was in was really good! Very tomato-ey

Overall such a great local spot in Soulard!

In town for a few days & wanted some Mexican food. The house rock margarita tasted good. I tried their tamales and they were alright. Was a little bit on the dry side. We also ordered the chicken quesadilla & cheese enchilada & they were just ok.

What a fantastic place or authentic mexican food.  FOH & BOH were on point throughout our entire meal.  The chips,  fried in lard, get-out-of-here! The table salsa was very tasty, too.  Our meals came in adequate time.  Enough time to relax, but not too much time to get antsy. The food was on point!  This truly is a great place in a historic section of St. Louis.  Take a little trip and give it  try.

I Love Some Good Authentic Mexican Food. First Time Visiting &This Place Did Not Disappoint! We Came On A Monday Evening &They Were Fairly Busy So For Our Party Of 5 We Decided On Outdoor Seating. (*Any Party Of 5+ You Will Get Charged Gratuity)  The Ambience For Their Outdoor Seating Was A Vibe.. Though The Actually Seating Is A Bit Reclined And You Have To Be Careful If People Walking By Will Bump You 🙂

- The Queso Is Really Good. (*If You Get Nachos., They Have Baked Cheese NOT Queso Cheese)
- I Decided On Chicken Enchiladas!

💲Price: ~ $13/Entree
👩🏾‍🍳 Customer Service: 3/10 ⭐️
🌮 Food: 5/10 ⭐️

You Can Definitely Tell By The Customer Service/Overall Vibe This Is A White Owned Establishment.

properties.adr_address: 727 N 1st St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Family-friendly chain eatery featuring traditional Italian entrees amid turn-of-the-century decor.

properties.formatted_address: 727 N 1st St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: The Old Spaghetti Factory

reviews.text:
Well we wanted a classic. Haven’t been in years but this was quite a treat. I really enjoy the classic look of the place. It bought back a lot of great memories.

We walked in, went down the stairs as instructed to check-in. We told a 10 minute wait and we would receive a text. The text never came so about 15 minutes later, we checked in again and they had trouble finding our name. However, the host still took care of us and had us seated.

Once seated, it was obvious that they were short staffed. I watched as people scrambled back and forth to serve their customers. However, our waiter Terry provided EXCELLENT customer service.

I ordered the Meat Lover’s Treat which is spaghetti. meatballs and Sicilian sausage. I will warn that this is an Italian restaurant and without the meat, the spaghetti is only sauce and noodles which is bland. That dish is about $16 and your meal is finished with ice cream. I attached a copy of the menu but it is very low light. Feel free to zoom in on the menu

Delicious food! Servers were very accommodating with special meal requests. Nice servers. Only gave three stars because 1) the wait was very long and once seated it was a long wait as well and 2) the ambiance was out dated in terms of the decor, the place needs a renovation for sure it hasn't been updated since the 70s looks like, and the bathroom area smelled weird like urine to me.

The atmosphere is so much fun at The Old Spaghetti Factory in St. Louis. The parking is close by which is nice if it is really cold outside. The chicken marsala was delicious that I tried and of course you have to eat the spumoni ice cream after your entrée. We will definitely be back. We had a big group and if I am remembering correctly our orders were all right.
Excellent service, relaxed atmosphere, really good food, and bar. It was worth the 45-minute wait. It's a little pricey but still good value.

It was fine. I expected much better. The ambience makes you feel like you’re in some old school vintage place. I’m not sure if our server was new, but the waters took 20 mins, didn’t receive our bread or salad until she came around 20 mins later asking do you want more bread, and we had informed her. Once we got the salad, our entree came out 2 mins after so we couldn’t even start the salad and now there’s plates shoved for us. Bread seemed stale, forgot the meatballs, had to correct it. Overall not a great experience, won’t go again.

Pros of the experience: noodles were cooked to perfection. The orange crème soda was heavenly.

properties.adr_address: 3137 Morgan Ford Rd, St. Louis, MO 63116-1933, USA
properties.formatted_address: 3137 Morgan Ford Rd, St. Louis, MO 63116, USA
properties.name: Grand Pied

reviews.text:
Absolutely one of the best meals I've had. The French Onion soup is probably the best I've ever had. The beginettes with sausage gravy.... OMG! SO GOOD! My hubby had the pancakes. They were seriously some of the best pancakes EVER! He also had the grits with the cheese and dirty gravy add on and they were absolutely delicious!
Jackie, our server, was kind, friendly, and attentive. Chef Tony is phenomenal! If you're on the fence about dining here, RUN - don't walk to get there! Just prepare yourself as you will have found a new favorite restaurant!!

Loved everything and everyone!  The server team is so nice!  The outside patio was shaded and lovely.  The FOOD!  amazing!  Get the pancakes and do NOT share.  We did share the beignets, there were plenty.  Sausage is homemade, I usually find sausage a bit too greasy but not here!  Sorry I don’t have a photo we wanted to dig in!  Update, hubby took photos!!
We had the Gumbo and Grits, the slinger, and the French onion soup for Brunch. So delicious.  Cute little place with great atmosphere. Also try the Brown sugar oatmilk shaken espresso, very yummy.

Excellent pancakes and sauces. And the people inside were so kind— I needed a double order instead of a single order and a patron inside let me have his order since he had the time to wait. My jaw dropped, I was rushing to an appointment and they facilitated that. There are still good people in the world.

They had a sign out front saying "BEST PANCAKES IN STL" - I have to agree!
GOOD PANCAKES SERVED HERE!
Really yummy food here with a step above in terms of quality and taste.

I had a sandwich here for lunch too a while ago and it was really good. They had these super thick fries with the sandwich and it was bomb.

(Extra points for a cool bathroom :p)

UPDATE:
- The slinger is bomb too! -see last photos
- I don't know why they gave me this mug.... WHAT DO THEY KNOW ABOUT ME?!?? 😆

properties.formatted_address: 827 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Washington Avenue Bistro

reviews.text: The Ladies that work there where so helpful, sweet, and attentive. This is a place everyone should visit, a very relaxing experience.
Excellent Service, Excellent Food

properties.adr_address: 1317 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Generous portions of American & Greek food in an unpretentious setting.

properties.formatted_address: 1317 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Friends Bar & Grill

reviews.text:
Attempted to visit Friends twice before, but was always unsure how much of a "restaurant" they were. The seating is limited, unless there is more somewhere I didn't see which is possible. They run the front with a bartender/server. What I could see one cook, a lady at that. (which I love to see) No complaints here, bartender/manager? was on his game pre bussing and having tables wiped down as soon as the table was checked out and gone.

Let's talk food. OMG!! First things first, we WILL be back!! The burger... all I had was a single and it is MASSIVE one pound!! I like a good chair broiled burger, but for being a flat top burger phenominal. Steak fries!! And the wings, come breaded or non can be bought individually. DELICIOUS. Kids pizza is the best kids pizza I've had ANYWHERE and if you follow me you know we are a family that likes to eat so we know.

Great place.

First time trying this  establishment, my son recommended it to me, said they had good burgers, and large portions so I decided to try them for myself. He was right burgers were large enough for me to be full with 1/2 of, save the rest for lunch the next day. I would have given them 5 stars except I felt for almost $5 an order, they could have given more onion rings, which were btw, delicious, some of the best I've tasted. I must just be greedy!!! 😅😅😅

Wow, new to downtown but a great addition!
These burgers are the bomb. Hand formed patties with a perfect texture on great light buns. The salad was huge and delicious.
Overall, this will be your go-to burger place.

Quiet little place that makes you feel at home. Food was unbelievably amazing and bigger then I expected. Staff was extremely friendly and even offered a yummy shot after our lunch. We will definitely be sharing our wonderful experience and we will be back soon.... they gained some loyal customers today.

This place is brand new relocating from another location.  Food portions are huge which is apparently a norm which I appreciated.  Shuttle driver (Brian!) suggested the place after a hockey game.  I appreciated the kitchen staying open late during the week.  They're obviously not ready yet, bar needs stocked and the space is still getting prepped.  Tried a beef and chicken philly.  Fries great, side salad HUGE, Phillies were a little dry but excellent the next day.  Can't wait to try some other menu items and hope they keep the kitchen open late on game days.

properties.adr_address: 1405 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.formatted_address: 1405 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Kitchen 4AM

reviews.text: Great atmosphere! Lovely decor! Food was pleasing to even my daughter's immature palate. Quite a few items that were on the menu they did not have available - specifically their "signature" drink.

AMAZING! FLAVORFUL! First time dining here was for my birthday dinner on Saturday. There was a slight wait (large party). However, once the food arrived, it was beyond my expectations!!! Amazing. Loved it so much came back for Sunday Brunch!! Liquor license would have made it 5 stars!!

If you have ever read any of my reviews, you are aware, I've traveled extensively and eaten at numerous restaurants.

With that said, this restaurant blew me away. The food and service was excellent! Our server Mercedes did a great job!

Every dish I tasted was delicious and I devoured them 😋. I'm especially fond of Lamb Chops and their's were excellent. The meat was juciy and tasty, hats off to the Chef 👨🏾‍🍳.

As of today, 4 AM would be my number one restaurant recommendation 👑 in St.Louis for friends, family and out of town quest.

Give them a try you will not be disappointed...

My food was absolutely delicious. I had crab fries and the cajun pasta with shrimp and lobster.  I gave 4 stars because they didn't have the duck wings that were on the menu,  and I really wanted to try them. The staff was very welcoming and professional.  I will definitely spread the word and be returning soon.

This was my first time at the restaurant and the experience wasn’t great . They have no liquor so if you want a drink with ur meal that is out of the question . It was only one waitress serving the entire restaurant it was multiple people leaving out upset because of the bad service and the wait time . The reason I gave a two star rating  is because of their pasta  it was definitely amazing

properties.adr_address: 8815 N Broadway, St. Louis, MO 63147-2216, USA
properties.formatted_address: 8815 N Broadway, St. Louis, MO 63147, USA
properties.name: Cuszos stl

reviews.text: Like, honestly hats off to the creator of this elegant food, not to many places Lin stk has been consistently carrying about the food, it’s like routine cooking. I got a different experience, and then the food is like originally made from their restaurant. I can see and can’t wait for the takeover of the food business I see lights around cuzzos!!..

Delicious!! Service is amazing, our waitress really knows her menu like full menu what each meal is made of.  Definitely will come back here when we visit again.  This is a must go to place.  One stop shop great food and good drinks!!
Had the salmon pasta and wings it was fire🔥. You wouldnt expect food like that out a gas station. Dont judge a book by its cover. Definitely will return.

Food is so good  ..not your typical gas station food ...haven't gotten anything I haven't enjoyed only complaint I have is I wish they stayed open later ..other than that I highly recommend this place ..
Great quality food so tasty and fresh and definitely worth the price.

properties.adr_address: 4145 Manchester Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Family-owned establishment serving Nepalese, Korean & Indian cuisines in understated quarters.

properties.formatted_address: 4145 Manchester Ave, St. Louis, MO 63110, USA
properties.name: Everest Cafe & Bar

reviews.text: One of the best Indian restaurants in town. I typically go for the lunch buffet and they have a great assortment of authentic items (mean and vegetarian), would be somewhat standard but the flavor of everything and how it is cooked is very very good! Friendly service and in a great location as welling being in the middle of the grove. Can walk to breweries, bars, parks, and hang out spots near by.

I the lunch buffett today.  What AMAZING food!!!  It has been a few years since I have been to Everest Cafe.  They have expanded the restaurant.  They have done a TERRIFIC with all the updates.  EVERY dish tasted DELICIOUS and FANTASTIC !!!  All the flavors were INCREDIBLE!!!  Make sure to eat at Everest Cafe, you will NOT BE DISAPPOINTED!!!

Got pork Momoa(?)
Tandoori Chicken - really big portion
Chicken tikka masala

Super delicious. All of the dishes were flavorful

We were a party of two and we took most of the tandoori chicken to go.

Definitely worth it !!
we will be coming back again to try the other dishes.

My wife and I dined in and enjoyed the lunch buffet. We tried a little bit of everything and everything was fantastic.

One of the things I enjoyed the most was experiencing the regional variations on popular dishes such as chicken tikka masala, or chicken korma. Surprising to me, one of the things I enjoyed the most was the vegetable korma.

The food was top notch, the service was impeccable and my wife and I look forward to visiting again.
We enjoyed samosa appetizer, veggie chow-chow, and tama bodi ra alu tarkari. Service was good, food was delicious and fresh. Will go back to try other vegan options.

properties.adr_address: 1820 Market St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Historic eatery set in Union Station Hotel & offering traditional American cooking.

properties.formatted_address: 1820 Market St, St. Louis, MO 63103, USA
properties.name: Station Grille

reviews.text: This is a nice restaurant. The wait staff was very friendly. They have a buffet for breakfast with a nice omelet bar. You really can’t beat the classic look and feel of the restaurant. I recommend eating here while having a stay at the famous Union Station hotel. You won’t regret it.

Had breakfast here 2 days and were lucky enough to get Flori as our waiter both days! He's half the reason we went back,  excellent friendly service! We did the buffet one of the days (excellent omelet) and Individual meals the other day which were also pretty good! The food was nothing outstanding but the prices and service along with the food made it a good all around experience!

We ate here for breakfast this past Wednesday.  Best omelette I’ve had.  I believe our chef’s name was Mark, super friendly, great experience!  I’m a picky eater and Mark was great about all my requests.  Great job!

We had lunch, which looked and tasted great (vegan Thai noodles and burger with salad) and was very reasonably priced. Service was terrific. Glad we bothered to walk around the block after going to the aquarium, since you can’t get directly into the hotel from there if you’re not a guest.

Came here for breakfast, and hats off to our omelette chef!  I believe his name was Mark. Made the best omelette I’ve ever had!! He was extremely nice and gave us some great ideas for some attractions to check out in St. Louis. I would come back just because of the service I received from him! Great job!

properties.adr_address: 1013 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Casual, modern spot offers an eclectic array of Japanese fare including sushi, plus burgers.

properties.formatted_address: 1013 Washington Ave, St. Louis, MO 63101, USA
properties.name: Mizu Sushi Bar

reviews.text: The food was delicious and the service was excellent!  We were going to share a bowl of the chicken ramen and they even offered to split it into 2 different bowls for us. The sushi was so tasty and the spring rolls were fresh and delicious with the side of peanut sauce 😋 The ramen had a nice, spicy kick to it. It's not like the traditional ramen you'd find in Japan, but it was yummy! Definitely would recommend this spot!

Came with a group for girl's night out and the service was extremely slow. Although I'm fairly certain there was only one server. The food was okay. I ordered gyoza, California roll and spring rolls. The spring rolls were the best part of the meal. Very crispy and well made. The sweet dipping sauce was a perfect pairing. The dumplings were good as well. The sushi was okay. The imitation crab was not great. Not to mention one person at my table had hair in her food. A couple of orders were wrong. If you're looking for a place with fast, dependable service, this is definitely not the place to go. And hopefully your dish doesn't have hair 🤷🏿‍♀️

I want to point out that the water here is impeccable. Many restaurants have poor water. This water tastes purified. So fresh. I imagine The fountain of youth tastes just like this. Like.. I be looking for that taste in every restaurant. If the water is good, you know the food is gonna BUSSSS.

Everything is good about this place. I’ve had the ramen everytime I’ve went and it’s so spicy and good! Great flavor. I’ve had the chicken and the beef. The chicken is my favorite tho. That broth was just impeccable.

I didn’t like that I read that the ramen noodles were like the thin noodles you get in a .20 cent pack at the grocery and that’s false. These are thicker than those. Thick enough. They’re not the thicker ramen noodles I’ve had at other places BUT are they better? ABSOLUTELY. I get extremely full before I finish my bowl so that’s all that matters.

When food makes you happy and hopeful all of a sudden after eating you know it’s good. This place definitely brings bliss and they have amazing prices!!

I had the rainbow roll too. Delicious. Fresh. I added eel sauce. I was SO full.
We went here for lunch, and grabbed the rainbow sushi roll, a variety sushi plate, and lemon drops! Everything was delicious, and the owner is so sweet - she served us and treated us great!❤️
Loved the food and drinks. We asked the server to bring us a surprise sushi roll, and what she brought was AMAZING. Will definitely go back.

properties.adr_address: 1000 Spruce St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Lofty, industrial hangout with 2 bars & creative pub grub, plus weekend brunch & TVs showing sports.

properties.formatted_address: 1000 Spruce St, St. Louis, MO 63102, USA
properties.name: Wheelhouse Downtown

reviews.text: Awesome spot to grab brunch with a large group and then hit a cardinals ball game. The food is actually better than you would expect for what truly is a bar that functions sort of as a night club as well. Great location if you’re doing anything downtown to stop in eat and walk most places after!

The atmosphere was fun with great music and friendly staff. The drinks were delicious but the food wasn't great. It was edible, but didn't tickle the taste buds. I would still recommend trying this place out. It's a vibe and the atmosphere and drinks make it worth it!

My first time going for brunch. The food and drinks were great with great service. The place was a little louder than I expected but the DJ was doing a great job. I only wished I didn't have to yell to have a conversation during brunch.

My food was delicious! I got the pork lovers scramble. It seemed like there could've been more of a serving. It was kind of a small amount.
What was most shocking though was the atmosphere, which is what I didn't expect. It was like a club in there, and I went at 2pm on a Sunday. The music was loud and bumping and it was very crowded. Ppl were outside trying to get in but they were full. (Get a reservation. I got right in.) They even checked my ID at the door. It might be fun for a night out but not your average Sunday brunch.

Definitely a college scene. They check IDs to enter however they had little kids in high chairs at the table. I came for brunch for a party of 11 which was a disaster. We waited forever for one of the large parties to leave but they stayed beyond the two hour limit and so we were told we’d get two tables close together which ended up being two tables on opposite ends of the dining area. The music was so loud it probably wouldn’t have mattered if we were seated close together because you can’t hear anything.  The food wasn’t worth the wait and could definitely use some seasoning. I ordered the brunch burger which for some reason it’s Canadian Bacon or no bacon at all because you can’t sub for regular bacon. Our waitress gave us dirty silverware with a hair on it and never came back to check on us. The bottomless mimosas are the one redeeming quality. I paid like $50 total for a basic brunch. I don’t mind the 20% automatic gratuity but if you’re going to do that make sure the service and the food is up to par. I’ve had better meals at Cracker Barrel. The restaurant space itself is pretty so I give them points for style. Bottom line: Definitely not at the top of my list of places to go. There are much better places to Brunch at in STL
